 ('62', '62', 'en_us', 'Apply for a Disabled Parking Blue Zone', '', '<h3>Disabled Parking&nbsp;Blue Zone&nbsp;Program</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>A Blue Zone&nbsp;provides on-street parking for people with disabilities. The Blue Zone&nbsp;has a painted blue curb with a posted sign.</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<p>Residents and businesses can request Blue Zones&nbsp;from the Disabled Parking Zone program.<br>The City does not install “Blue Zones&nbsp;for paratransit drop-off and pick-up.</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<p>To learn more, please read the Policy summaries below.</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<p><br><a href=\"http://www2.oaklandnet.com/oakca1/groups/pwa/documents/policy/oak051830.pdf\">Residential Blue Zone Policy Summary<br></a><a href=\"http://www2.oaklandnet.com/oakca1/groups/pwa/documents/policy/oak051829.pdf\">Non-Residential Blue Zone Policy Summary</a></p>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', NULL, 'information', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2015-12-18 21:40:10', '2016-03-01 18:36:01', '0ef0babd-6f37-4f85-a36e-838481207a96'),
 ('72', '72', 'en_us', 'Apply for a Parking Obstruction Permit', '​Do you need to block parking spaces or traffic? If your portable storage unit or moving truck will block parking on a public street or right of way, you will need an Obstruction Permit.', '<p>An Obstruction Permit allows you to park the pod, portable storage unit or moving truck in one site for a limited amount of time.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3 id=\"how-the-obstruction-permit-works\">How the Obstruction Permit Works</h3>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n  <li>The Obstruction Permit tells nearby property owners that they can not park in the permitted site for a limited amount of time.</li>\r\n  <li>You may only block the street or right of way that you are moving from or to.</li>\r\n  <li>You need to post the NO PARKING sign(s) that you receive with the Obstruction Permit at least 72 hours (3 days) before parking the portable storage unit or moving truck.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<h3 id=\"how-to-apply-for-an-obstruction-permit\">How to Apply for an Obstruction Permit</h3>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<p>You can only apply for an Obstruction Permit in person at the Permit Center. To avoid long line, visit the Permit Center early in the day before the busiest time from 11 a.m. to 4 p.m.</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n  <li>Please bring the following information.</li>\r\n  <li>Site address.</li>\r\n  <li>Dates required.</li>\r\n  <li>Number of parking spaces required. One parking space is 25 feet long.</li>\r\n  <li>Meter numbers if you are blocking parking meters</li>\r\n  <li>Contact phone number for the company or person applying.</li>\r\n  <li>If related to work requiring permit, please reference permit application number.</li>\r\n  <li>Traffic control plan (only required if you need to block traffic)</li>\r\n  <li>Refer to the Traffic Engineering website(http://www2.oaklandnet.com/Government/o/PWA/o/EC/o/TS/OAK026469).</li>\r\n  <li>Visit the Permit Center</li>\r\n  <li>Once you arrive at the Permit Center’s Information Counter, ask for an Obstruction Permit.</li>\r\n  <li>When your number is called, proceed to the indicated counter.</li>\r\n  <li>Provide the required information</li>\r\n  <li>Pay the permit fee</li>\r\n  <li>The Permit Center accepts cash, checks payable to the City of Oakland and most major credit cards.</li></ol>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<h3 id=\"cost-of-the-obstruction-permit\">Cost of the Obstruction Permit</h3>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<p>The cost of an Obstruction Permit varies. The cost depends on the period of time for the permit, the number of parking spaces required and the type of parking spaces blocked. \r\nFor more information, please call the Permit Center at (510) 238-3443.</p>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', NULL, 'information', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2015-12-18 21:58:04', '2016-03-01 18:36:01', '13e70aaa-fdd0-42d3-bd86-7db44e6a95b1'),
 ('92', '92', 'en_us', 'Apply for a Residential Parking Permit', '', '<p>You can apply for a parking permit through the Residential Parking Permit (RPP) program. This permit will allow you park your vehicle in certain neighborhoods in Oakland. You need to register your vehicle to an eligible address to receive the permit.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3 id=\"what-you-need-to-know-before-applying\">What You Need to Know Before Applying</h3>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n  <li>To see if your address is eligible, go to__<strong>__</strong><strong>__</strong>_____</li>\r\n  <li>Make sure your address on your vehicle’s registration and driver’s license is up to date.<ol><li>Click here to update your address with the DMV online. (http://dmv.ca.gov/online/onlinesvcs.htm)</li></ol><ol><li>After updating your address, print the confirmation.</li></ol><ol><li>Submit this confirmation with your application.</li></ol></li>\r\n  \r\n  \r\n  \r\n  <li>Clear all unpaid parking tickets from the City of Oakland.</li></ol>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<h3 id=\"how-to-apply-for-a-residential-parking-permit\">How to Apply for a Residential Parking Permit</h3>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<p>You need to submit an application, four supporting documents and the correct fee to apply. The address on your application must match the address on each supporting document.</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<h3>Parking&nbsp;Citation&nbsp;Assistance Center&nbsp;Hours</h3>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<p>Mondays, Tuesdays, Thursdays and Fridays from 9 a.m. to 4:30 p.m.<br>Wednesdays from 9:30 a.m. to 4:30 p.m.</p>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', NULL, 'information', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2015-12-18 22:05:30', '2016-03-01 18:36:01', 'a4eb5ab1-fc9f-4149-8e37-24e1581b9399'),
 ('112', '112', 'en_us', 'Renew Your Residential Parking Permit', '', '<p>You can renew your permit online if you received a letter that says you are eligible for online renewal.</p>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', NULL, 'information', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2015-12-18 22:16:30', '2016-03-01 18:36:02', 'e37ed58e-4f3a-4c3a-954e-cac6cb08c864'),
 ('122', '122', 'en_us', 'Pay or Contest Parking Tickets', 'What to do if you receive a parking ticket and want to pay or contest it', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '[]', NULL, 'information', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2015-12-18 22:42:23', '2016-03-01 18:36:02', 'af918738-099e-4a5b-ba69-8844f6db200c'),
 ('132', '132', 'en_us', 'Contest a Parking Ticket', '', '<h2>Contesting by fax, in person, or by mail</h2><p><a href=\"\">Download and complete the </a><a href=\"http://www2.oaklandnet.com/oakca1/groups/cityadministrator/documents/form/oak041670.pdf\">Contest Form</a> or write a letter of explanation for contesting your citation.\r\nPlease include your name, address, telephone number, current mailing address and parking ticket citation number.</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<p>Keep a copy of your ticket for your records.\r\nReturn your Contest Form or letter, along with the original parking ticket and additional documents in Person, by Mail, or by Fax.</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<ul><li>Please wait 48 hours from the time of issuance to ensure your citation is entered into the online system.</li><li>It may take handwritten tickets up to two weeks to be entered into the online system.</li><li>You must contest your ticket within 21 days of the date of issuance.</li><li>You’ll need to upload up to three documents that provide evidence to support your written testimony.</li></ul>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<h3 id=\"what-happens-next\">What Happens Next</h3>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n  <li>The Parking Citation Assistance Center investigates your ticket.</li>\r\n  <li>You will be notified of the decision by mail.</li>\r\n  <li>If the ticket is upheld, you will have 21 days to pay your ticket or request an Administrative Hearing.</li>\r\n  <li>If you contested a parking ticket and you are not satisfied with the decision, you can <a href=\"{entry:182:url}\">request an Administrative Hearing</a>.</li>\r\n</ol>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '[]', NULL, 'information', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2015-12-18 22:46:27', '2016-03-01 18:36:02', '3218095c-9f09-4820-ad0e-a2e54c1973b6'),
 ('142', '142', 'en_us', 'Jobs', 'Finding jobs and employment services in Oakland.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '[]', NULL, 'information', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p>\"It\'s a great place to work because of the quality of people who work here and because of the residents. You gotta love the variety and personality.\"</p><p>- Glassdoor&nbsp;Reviewer</p>', '<p>\"If you live in Oakland, it\'s great to be a public servant in your own town.\"</p><p>- Glassdoor&nbsp;Reviewer<br></p>', '<p>\"There is potential to do great things in this City and most of the employees want to do just that.\"</p><p>- Glassdoor&nbsp;Reviewer<br></p>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2015-12-18 23:04:13', '2016-03-01 18:36:02', 'b31e230f-302e-49c2-a82a-c12e8a23cd89'),
 ('152', '152', 'en_us', 'Set up a Parking Citation Alert', '', '<p>Parking citation alerts provide notifications to help manage your parking needs and avoid unnecessary penalties. When you create an account, it will alert you so you receive notifications about:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n  <li>\r\n    <p>When a new citation is issued to your vehicle</p>\r\n  </li>\r\n  <li>\r\n    <p>Before a penalty are applied</p>\r\n  </li>\r\n  <li>\r\n    <p>After a mail-in payment is applied</p>\r\n  </li>\r\n  <li>\r\n    <p>About upcoming hearings</p>\r\n  </li>\r\n  <li>\r\n    <p>Before you become “Boot Eligible”</p>\r\n  </li>\r\n  <li>\r\n    <p>Upcoming Resident Parking Permit Renewal</p>\r\n  </li>\r\n  <li>\r\n    <p>City of Oakland Parking announcements</p></li></ul>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '[]', NULL, 'information', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2015-12-18 23:08:02', '2016-03-01 18:36:02', '1093efcd-b938-4a7f-ab26-567a53766b28'),
 ('162', '162', 'en_us', 'Apply for Jobs', 'The process of applying for a job with the City, requirements, job listings and applications', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '[]', NULL, 'information', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2015-12-18 23:09:39', '2016-03-01 18:36:02', 'ae5a9777-75e0-47b4-86be-5b33c299d07e'),
 ('182', '182', 'en_us', 'Request an Administrative Hearing', 'If you contested a parking ticket and you are not satisfied with the decision, you can request an Administrative Hearing either by phone or submitting the form in person or by mail.', '<h3>What You Need to Know</h3>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n  <li>Once you receive the decision from contesting your ticket, you have 21 days to schedule a hearing.</li>\r\n  <li>You can request a hearing either in person or or by mail.</li>\r\n  <li>You must pay a deposit equal to the amount of the fine before scheduling a hearing.</li></ul>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<h3 id=\"what-happens-next\">What Happens Next</h3>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n  <li>You will receive a notice by mail with the date and time of the hearing.</li>\r\n  <li>All hearings are held Monday through Friday between 9 a.m. and 4 p.m.</li>\r\n  <li>The hearing will be held at:</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Eastmont Mall Police Substation</strong><br>2651 73rd Avenue, Upper Level<br>Oakland, CA</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<p>If you cannot attend your scheduled hearing, you have two options:</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<h3 id=\"rescheduling-a-hearing\">Rescheduling a Hearing</h3>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<p>You have two options if you cannot attend the scheduled hearing:</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Reschedule the hearing</strong></p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<p>Call the Hearing Department at (510) 238-4484 at least five calendar days before the scheduled hearing.</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Request a hearing by mail</strong></p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<p>Send a letter detailing your dispute and include all the required documentation.</p>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '[]', NULL, 'information', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2015-12-18 23:16:35', '2016-03-01 18:36:03', '289a14de-aee8-44b4-8f89-bed398525d4b'),
 ('192', '192', 'en_us', 'Benefits & Perks', 'Salary information, benefits and compensation for City employees', '<h2>Health Care Coverage</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>All employees are eligible for health care coverage for themselves and their eligible dependents. These plans may include health insurance (medical coverage), dental care, and vision care.</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<h2>Summary of Benefits</h2>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<div class=\"table-wrap\">\r\n<table><thead><tr><th></th><th>Health</th><th>Dental</th><th>Vision Care</th><th>Worker\'s&nbsp;Comp</th><th>Disability Insurance</th><th>Life Insurance</th><th>Retirement</th><th>Professional Development</th><th>Unemployment Insurance</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Full-time employee (Not include fire and police)</td><td>x</td><td>x</td><td>x</td><td>x</td><td>x</td><td>x</td><td>x</td><td>x</td><td>x</td></tr><tr><td>Fire and&nbsp;Police (full-time)</td><td>x</td><td>x</td><td></td><td>x</td><td></td><td>x</td><td>x</td><td></td><td>x</td></tr><tr><td>Part-time</td><td>x</td><td></td><td></td><td>x</td><td>x</td><td></td><td>x</td><td></td><td>x</td></tr><tr><td>Part-time Senior Aides</td><td>x</td><td></td><td></td><td>x</td><td></td><td></td><td>x</td><td></td><td></td></tr></tbody></table>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<h3><br>What to Know</h3>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<ul><li>You are eligible to enroll on the date you are hired.</li><li>Work with your department to enroll within 60 days.<p><br></p>\r\n<ul><li>If you wait more than 60 days to enroll, you will face a penalty of a 90 day waiting period.</li></ul></li><li>Your coverage starts on the first of the month after submission of your paperwork.</li><li>You can change your plan during open enrollment during the fall.</li><li>Any changes you make become effective in January of the following year.</li></ul>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<h3>Medical Coverage</h3>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<p>You can choose a medical plan through CalPERS (California Public Employees Retirement Systems) Health Benefit Services.<br>The City pays the full monthly premium for some plans. For other plans, the employee pays premiums with after-tax dollars.<br>For more information on medical plans, visit the CalPERS website.</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<p><br></p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<h2>Dental Plans</h2>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<p>All full time employees except fire and police can choose from two dental plans for themselves and their eligible dependents. The HMO dental plan includes no deductibles when visiting an authorized dentist. This plan is administered by DeltaCare.<br>The PPO plan covers a percentage of costs but gives members more flexibility. This plan is administered by Delta Dental. <br>Police and fire personnel have dental coverage through their respective unions.</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<h2>Vision Care</h2>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<p>All full time employees except fire and police have vision coverage for themselves and their eligible dependents. This plan is administered by Vision Service Plan.<br>Police and fire personnel do not have vision coverage.</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<h2>Dependents</h2>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<p>Your dependents may be eligible for the same health care coverage that you enroll in.</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<p>Eligible dependents include:</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<ul><li>Spouse</li><li>Domestic partner</li><li>Financially dependent children\r\n<ul><li>Medical benefits: Children under age 26</li></ul><ul><li>Dental and vision benefits: Children under age 18 or students age 19 - 25</li></ul></li></ul>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<p>You need to provide documentation to add your dependents to your health plan.</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<ul><li>Marriage certificate</li><li>Certificate of domestic partnership</li><li>Birth certificate</li><li>Legal adoption or guardianship papers</li><li>Affidavit for financially dependent children</li><li>Proof of full-time enrollment in school</li></ul>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<h2>Continuing Your Benefits</h2>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<p>Under COBRA, an employee and enrolled dependents may pay to continue medical, dental or vision coverage for a limited period of time if city-paid coverage ceases for reasons recognized under the law.<br>The cost for COBRA coverage equals the same premium the City pays monthly plus a 2% administrative fee.</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<h2>Retirement</h2>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<p>All employees of the City of Oakland have retirement benefits through the Public Employees\' Retirement System (CalPERS).<br>What happens to my CalPERS benefits if I leave the City?</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<p>You may be able to take your retirement benefits with you. If you leave the City to work for another employer that also participates in CalPERS, your retirement benefit will continue. If your new employer does not participate in CalPERS, the funds may be rolled over into a qualified Individual Retirement Account (IRA). <br>Current and former City employees interested in learning more about their retirement benefits may contact CalPERS directly at (888)225-7377 or visit the CalPERS website at www.calpers.ca.gov. They may also contact the City of Oakland\'s Retirement Office at (510)238-6479, weekdays from 8:30am - 5:00pm.</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<h3>Deferred Compensation</h3>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<p>The Deferred Compensation Plan is a voluntary retirement plan. You can increase your retirement savings and reduce your tax burden by contributing to this 457(b) plan.<br>You can contribute as little as $10 per pay period. The maximum contribution allowed is defined by Federal regulations for the calendar year. You can choose from several investment options. The City does not contribute to nor match employee contributions to this plan.</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<h2>Life Insurance</h2>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<p>All full time employees including fire and police personnel have life insurance benefits. In the event of an employee\'s death, the beneficiary will receive an amount equal to the employee\'s current annual salary rounded up to the nearest $1,000. For example, if the annual salary is $35,500, the life insurance benefit would be $36,000.<br>If the death is the result of an accident, the beneficiary may receive an additional benefit equal to the life insurance amount.<br>The City pays the full premium cost for coverage. There is no employee contribution. Dependents are not eligible for this benefit.</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<h2><br>Disability</h2>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<p>Most part-time and full-time employees excluding police and fire personnel who experience a non-work-related illness or injury can apply for State Disability Insurance (SDI). This insurance is provided through the State of California\'s Employment Development Department.<br>Employees who do not qualify for SDI are covered by a third party administrator for both short- and long-term disability. Benefits begin after a seven-day period and are determined by several eligibility factors.</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<h2><br>Medical Waivers</h2>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<p>Upon proof of other medical coverage, employees may choose to waive or cancel medical benefits for themselves and eligible dependents and receive cash instead.</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<h2><br>Flexible Spending Accounts</h2>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<p>The City of Oakland offers three flexible spending programs: Medical Care Assistance Program (MCAP), Dependent Care Assistance Program (DCAP), Transit Program. <br>You contribute to these programs to pay for qualifying expenses with pre-tax dollars. This reduces the amount of tax dollars you pay. The IRS regulates these programs. Please visit the third party administrator website for specific information about the plans at http://www.cbadministrators.com.<br>The Medical Care Assistance Program (MCAP) allows an employee to pay for medical, dental and vision care expenses with pre-tax dollars up to $2,500 each year. Estimate your annual out-of-pocket medical costs to decide how much to contribute. The City will withhold contributions from your paycheck every two weeks.<br>The Dependent Care Assistance Program (DCAP) allows an employee to pay for dependent care expenses with pre-tax dollars up to $5000 per household. Only necessary dependent care that allows you, or both you and your spouse together, to work is eligible. Estimate your annual dependent-care costs to decide how much to contribute. The City will withhold contributions from your paycheck every two weeks.<br>After you pay for eligible expenses, submit a claim to the third party administrator for reimbursement.<br>The Transit Program allows an employee to pay for mass transit and parking with pre-tax dollars. Estimate your monthly transportation costs to decide how much to contribute. You may have to pay an administrative fee for the program.</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<p>The third party administrator will mail you a monthly voucher or transit card. You may use vouchers or transit cards at locations that accept tickets and passes. For more information, visit CBA, the third party administrator\'s website at http://www.cbadministrators.com.</p>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '[]', NULL, 'information', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2015-12-18 23:26:06', '2016-03-01 18:36:03', '03462828-1ce3-4183-bdc5-eca1f4964153'),
 ('202', '202', 'en_us', 'Application Process & Support', '', '<p>Working for the City of Oakland comes with many benefits!</p><ul><li>Job security</li><li>Diverse workforce</li><li>Benefits including health care coverage for you and your family</li></ul>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<p>The City manages hiring differently than private companies. Most hiring is guided by the Civil Service Board. Click here to learn more about the Civil Service Board.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The information below is provided to guide you through the hiring process and answer frequently asked questions. These guidelines describe the AVERAGE process for hiring through the Civil Service Board. You may want to bookmark this page for reference.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Your individual experience may differ from this process. If you have questions, please contact_______________________</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Stages of the hiring process<br></p>\r\n\r\n<ol><li>Search for open positions</li><li>Apply for a position</li><li>Application review</li><li>Civil service examination</li><li>Placement on eligibility list</li><li>Department interview</li><li>Receipt of job offer</li></ol>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<p>Read more below for details about each step in the process.</p><h2><br>1. Search for open positions</h2><p>\r\n\r\nThere are four ways that you can search for current job openings with the City of Oakland.<br></p><ol><li>Search online at Apply Online for Current Job Openings.</li><li>Visit City of Oakland offices to see posted job announcements.</li><li>Visit one of our One-Stop Career Centers throughout the City of Oakland.</li><li>Visit the City of Oakland Human Resources Department at 150 Frank H. Ogawa Plaza, 2nd Floor Suite 2352 from 8:30 am to 5:00 pm, Monday - Friday.</li></ol>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<p>If you don’t see a job you want yet, you can set up an alert to learn when a future job is posted. Complete a job interest card to receive this alert. For the next 12 months, you will receive an email when a new position matches the category you choose. &nbsp;</p><h2>2. Apply for a position</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>To apply to a specific position, you must submit your application online at Apply Online for Current Job Openings by the closing date. The Human Resources Department will email you to confirm receiving the application.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>If you do not have access to a computer or Internet access, you can use a computer at any location of the <a href=\"http://oaklandlibrary.org/using-library/locations-hours\">City of Oakland Public Library</a>. You can also use a work station of the City of Oakland Department of Human Resources Management at 150 Frank H. Ogawa Plaza, 2nd Floor, Oakland, CA 94612 from 9 am to 5 pm.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Need help applying? Call NeoGov at (877) 204-4442 for technical questions. For all other questions, call (510) 238-3112, TTY 238-3254.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Veterans:</strong> You may be entitled to preference points which can help you get hired. To receive your points, you must have an honorable discharge. Submit Form DD214 with your application on or before the final filing date for the position. If you are a disabled veteran, submit proof of your disability from the Veteran’s Service with your application.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>People with Criminal Convictions:</strong> You can still apply to a job with the City of Oakland. Each application will be given individual consideration, based on job-relatedness. All records of conviction(s) will be reviewed. This review may result in a request for additional information or termination if needed.</p><h2>3. Application review</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>Once your application is submitted, it will be reviewed in two stages.</p><ol><li>Review of minimum qualifications: The Human Resources Department will check that your experiences fits the qualifications listed in the job posting. If your application satisfies the criteria, it will move to the next stage.</li><li>Review of supplemental questions: Depending on the criteria of the job you applied to, you may be required to complete supplemental questions. You must complete these questions if the job announcement says that the questions are required. If these required questions are not answered, your application will not be considered. If the questions are optional, it is best to answer the questions as completely as possible. These responses may help your application move to the next stage of the hiring process.</li></ol>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<h2>4. Civil service examination</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>Examinations may include any combination of the following activities:</p><ul><li>Application Reviews</li><li>Review for Minimum Qualifications</li><li>Supplemental Questionnaire</li><li>Multiple Choice/True-False Written Test</li><li>Problem Exercise/ Writing Sample Test</li><li>Performance Test</li><li>Oral Interview</li></ul>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<p>The components of each examination are written in the job announcement for that examination.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The purpose of the examination is to further assess your knowledge and ability as well as your education, experience and other factors related to the job for which you applied. </p>\r\n\r\nExam Preparation <br><ul><li>Refer to test booklets on general test taking available at Oakland Public Library and local bookstores. The City does not offer exam preparation materials.</li></ul>\r\n\r\nOral Interview Preparation<br><ul><li>Review the job description for the position to become familiar with the position duties.</li><li>Be prepared to tell the interviewer about your education, work experience and qualifications as it relates to the position you have applied for</li></ul>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Persons with disabilities:</strong> Please contact the Human Resources Department if you need accommodations for the examination process. You will need to complete a form to share relevant information and what accommodation is required. &nbsp;Please attach a doctor\'s note.</p><h2><br>5. Placement on eligibility list</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>The eligibility list is a list of four people eligible for an open position in the hiring department. Candidates are listed in order based on their performance on the examination.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>To learn your score and rank on the eligibility list,</strong> forward a self address stamped envelope to the Human Resource Department with your request.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Once you are on an eligibility list, you can be sent on a maximum of four (4) job interviews with the hiring department. You can choose to decline up to three (3) different interviews for a position. After the third decline, your name will be removed from the eligibility list. </p>\r\n\r\n<p>If the hiring department does not select you, your name will stay on the eligibility list for up to two years for consideration for future positions in the hiring department.</p><h2><br>6. Department interview</h2>\r\n\r\n<h2>7. Receipt of job offer</h2>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<p>Congratulations on your new role at the City of Oakland!</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>\r\n\r\n<p> &nbsp;&nbsp;<br>12. How do I report a change of address?<br>Applicants can update their contact information at any time after logging into their NeoGov account. Current employees should fill out a <a href=\"http://www2.oaklandnet.com/Government/o/HumanResources/a/FAQ/OAK039854\">change of address form</a> and submit it to the Department of Human Resources Management 150 Frank H. Ogawa Plaza, Suite 2352 Oakland CA, 94612.<br> <br>20. How do I obtain information about benefits for the job I am applying for?<br>Contact the Human Resource Department Benefits Unit at (510) 238-7295, TTY 238-3254 for Medical, Dental, Insurance, Employee Wellness and Deferred Compensation information.</p>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '[]', NULL, 'information', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2015-12-18 23:30:33', '2016-03-01 18:36:03', '10b9a05f-4c95-4660-aed3-2b05e7a07ed9'),
 ('212', '212', 'en_us', 'Apply Online for Current Job Openings', '', '<p>Thank you for your interest in working for the City of Oakland!</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<ul><li>For current City of Oakland or Port of Oakland employees, click here to view openings.</li><li>For&nbsp;Port of Oakland jobs, click here to see available openings.</li></ul>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<h3 id=\"how-to-get-started-first-time-applicants\">How to Get Started: First-Time Applicants</h3>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n  <li>Search for jobs that fit your skills and interests.</li>\r\n  <li>Save your search by setting up a job alert in a Job Interest Card.</li>\r\n  <li>This will send you emails when new jobs open that fit your search criteria.</li>\r\n  <li>Click the “Apply” link of a job you are interested in.</li>\r\n  <li>Create an account.</li>\r\n  <li>Select a username and password.</li>\r\n  <li>Click the “Build Job Application” link to start your application.</li>\r\n  <li>Save your application as you complete sections.</li>\r\n  <li>The NeoGov system will save your information every 15 minutes.</li>\r\n  <li>You can save and use your application to apply for other job openings.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<p><em>Online applications are stored on a secure site. Only authorized employees and hiring authorities have access to the information submitted.</em></p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<h3 id=\"tips-for-completing-your-application\">Tips for Completing Your Application</h3>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n  <li>Review the supplemental questions, if any are included.</li>\r\n  <li>You may want to complete supplemental questions outside of the NeoGov system.</li>\r\n  <li>Other recommendations include:</li>\r\n  <li>Gather information about your education and work experience.</li>\r\n  <li>Provide specific information in your answers such as dates, locations, data, and references.</li>\r\n  <li>Write responses in a word processing program such as Microsoft Word.</li>\r\n  <li>Copy and paste these responses into the NeoGov system.</li>\r\n  <li>Complete and submit your application before the closing date for consideration.</li>\r\n</ul>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '[]', NULL, 'information', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2015-12-18 23:48:50', '2016-03-01 18:36:03', 'd0d060c4-c6a7-49de-8d42-5aa69e010c36'),
 ('222', '222', 'en_us', 'Remove the Boot from a Booted Vehicle', '', '<h3>What to Know</h3>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n  <li>Do not attempt to drive your vehicle because severe damage may occur.</li><li>The parking boot program targets the most serious parking violators who have&nbsp;<strong>five (5) or more unpaid parking tickets</strong>.</li><li>A sticker will be displayed on a window of your vehicle showing that your vehicle has been booted.</li>\r\n  <li>This sticker will include instructions in English, Chinese and Spanish.</li></ul>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n  <li>Phone assistance is available in multiple languages.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<h3 id=\"how-to-remove-the-boot-from-your-vehicle\">How to Remove the Boot from Your Vehicle</h3>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<p>Pay the fines for the unpaid tickets. You can make payments by phone or in person. In most cases, you can drive your vehicle in about five minutes. Payment plan options are available.</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<h4>By Phone</h4>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n  <li>Pay the fines with a credit/debit card or e-check.</li>\r\n  <li>The operator will provide a six-digit code.</li>\r\n  <li>This six-digit code will allow removal of the boot without damage to your vehicle.</li>\r\n  <li>Call the Help Center at (800) 500-6484 if you need assistance with boot removal steps.</li>\r\n  <li>Return the boot to the location provided by the Help Center.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<h4>In Person</h4>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n  <li>Pay the fines in cash.</li>\r\n  <li>You will receive a six-digit code.</li>\r\n  <li>This six-digit code will allow removal of the boot without damage to your vehicle.</li>\r\n  <li>Call the Help Center if you need assistance with boot removal steps.</li>\r\n  <li>Return the boot to the location provided by the Parking Assistance Center.</li></ol>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<h3>Hours</h3>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<p>Mondays, Tuesdays, Thursdays and Fridays from 9 a.m. to 4:30 p.m.<br>Wednesdays from 9:30 a.m. to 4:30 p.m.</p>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '[]', NULL, 'information', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2015-12-18 23:49:30', '2016-03-01 18:36:03', '30e7b84a-84a8-421a-9363-a3b563bc8d3a'),
 ('232', '232', 'en_us', 'Getting Your Towed Vehicle Released', '', '<p>If you believe your vehicle has been towed, please call A&B Vehicle Processing at (510) 635-3211 or visit <a href=\"http://www.abimpound.com./towed.html\">http://www.abimpound.com./towed.html</a> to confirm.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3 id=\"what-to-know\">What to Know</h3>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<p>A vehicle can be towed in Oakland for any of the following reasons:</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n  <li>A boot is placed on the vehicle, and payment for the boot fee and parking tickets have not been received</li>\r\n  <li>A vehicle registration (plate tag) has been expired for more than six (6) months</li>\r\n  <li>A vehicle has more than $2,500 in unpaid parking tickets</li>\r\n  <li>A vehicle has five (5) or more unpaid tickets in the State of California</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<h3 id=\"how-to-get-your-vehicle-released\">How to Get Your Vehicle Released</h3>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n  <li>Pay all of your unpaid parking tickets in Oakland. Payment plans are not available for towed vehicles.</li>\r\n  <li>Visit or call the Parking Citation Assistance Center to make payments.</li>\r\n  <li>Pay fees for towing and storage directly to the tow company.</li>\r\n  <li>You may need to pay unpaid tickets from all other cities in California to have your vehicle released.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<h3 id=\"for-more-information\">For More Information</h3>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<table>\r\n<thead>\r\n<tr><th>Location</th><th>Hours</th></tr>\r\n</thead>\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr><td style=\"background-color:white\">\r\nParking Citation Assistance Center\r\n\r\n250 Frank H. Ogawa Plaza, Suite 6300\r\n\r\nOakland, CA 94612\r\n\r\nPhone: (800) 500-6484\r\n</td><td>\r\nMondays, Tuesdays, Thursdays and Fridays from 9 a.m. to 4:30 p.m.\r\nWednesdays from 9:30 a.m. to 4:30 p.m.\r\n</td></tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<p>Only the registered owner of the towed vehicle can contest one or more of the unpaid tickets.</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<p>Please visit the Parking Citation Assistance Center at 250 Frank H. Ogawa Plaza, Suite 6300 or call the Center at (510) 238-4484.</p>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '[]', NULL, 'information', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2015-12-18 23:50:15', '2016-03-01 18:36:04', '744f10fd-c4e8-43ba-99ae-8a3629e5d73a'),
 ('252', '252', 'en_us', 'Additional Parking Information', 'When, where and how to legally park', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '[]', NULL, 'information', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2015-12-18 23:55:17', '2016-03-01 18:36:04', '76acd3a5-6305-4a8c-85a9-0c7bc4ca736f'),
 ('262', '262', 'en_us', 'Understanding Curb Colors', '', '<aside>\r\nPlease look for posted signs and curb colors when you park.\r\n\r\nFaded curb colors are still enforced.</aside>\r\n\r\n<table>\r\n<thead>\r\n<tr><th>Curb Color</th><th>Meaning</th></tr>\r\n</thead>\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr><td><strong>Red</strong></td><td>No stopping, standing or parking at any time</td></tr>\r\n<tr><td><strong>Yellow</strong></td><td>For loading and unloading of passengers and materials between 7 a.m. and 6 p.m. The loading or unloading of passengers should not exceed 3 minutes and the loading or unloading of materials from a vehicle with commercial plates should not exceed 30 minutes. \r\n\r\nThis parking restriction does not apply on Sundays and parking holidays.</td></tr>\r\n<tr><td><strong>White</strong></td><td>For loading and unloading of passengers which should not exceed three minutes. Most white curb restrictions apply from 7 a.m. to 6 p.m. except:\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Parking on a white curb in front of a hotel or hospital is restricted at all times.</li>\r\n<li>Parking in front of a theater, hall or other place of public assembly shall apply at all times except when the theater or hall is closed, and then a vehicle may park in the white zone for no longer than one hour.</li>\r\n</ul></td></tr>\r\n<tr><td><strong>Green</strong></td><td>No standing or parking for longer than 12 minutes at any time between 8 a.m and 6 p.m., excluding Sundays and parking holidays.</td></tr>\r\n<tr><td><strong>Blue</strong></td><td>For parking by physically handicapped person whose vehicles display either a valid placard or license plate for the disabled.</td></tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Please note - faded curb colors are still enforced.</strong> You can report a curb that needs repainting by reporting it to:</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Public Works Call Center</strong></p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<p>Phone: (510) 615-5566</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<p>Email: <a href=\"mailto://opwcallcenter@oaklandnet.com\">opwcallcenter@oaklandnet.com</a></p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<p>Online: <a href=\"http://gismaps.oaklandnet.com/srwebsite/ServiceType.aspx\">Report a Problem</a></p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<p>Mobile App: <a href=\"http://en.seeclickfix.com/oakland\">SeeClickFix</a></p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<p>For additional assistance with parking limitations for each curb color, please contact the Parking Citation Assistance Center at (800) 500-6484.</p>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '[]', NULL, 'information', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2015-12-18 23:56:20', '2016-03-01 18:36:04', '9ddc7bca-2b6b-44b9-b3d7-c3537aebd6bc'),
 ('272', '272', 'en_us', 'Find a City Owned Parking Garage', '', '<p>To find a City-owned garage or lot, check out the Oakland Parking Map above.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Please contact the parking operator if you have questions about a specific garage.</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<p>You can find contact information on the map below by clicking on the “P” linked to the garage.</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<p>A limited number of monthly parking permits are available at some metered outdoor lots. If you have questions about these permits, please call (510) 238-6154.</p>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '[]', NULL, 'information', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2015-12-18 23:57:44', '2016-03-01 18:36:04', '92d89807-5ec8-4a06-850d-307e25f58ccf'),
 ('282', '282', 'en_us', 'Parking Hours and Rates', '', '<aside>\r\nPlease look for posted signs and curb colors when you park.\r\n</aside>\r\n\r\n<p>Meter hours in Oakland, CA are Monday through Saturday from 8 a.m. to 6 p.m.</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<p>It costs $2 per hour to park at a parking meter.</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<p>Parking is free on the following holidays:</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n  <li>New Year’s Day - January 1</li>\r\n  <li>Martin Luther King, Jr. Birthday - Third Monday of January</li>\r\n  <li>President’s Day - Third Monday of February</li>\r\n  <li>Memorial Day - Last Monday of May</li>\r\n  <li>Independence Day - July 4</li>\r\n  <li>Labor Day - First Monday of September</li>\r\n  <li>Thanksgiving Day - Fourth Thursday of November</li>\r\n  <li>Christmas Day - December 25</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<p>If any of these holidays falls upon a Sunday, the following Monday is a holiday.</p>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '[]', NULL, 'information', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2015-12-18 23:59:19', '2016-03-01 18:36:04', '3c7d954e-2e21-4576-92a4-14f29a325129'),
 ('292', '292', 'en_us', 'Street Sweeping Restrictions', '', '<p>Please look for street sweeping signs and curb colors when you park.The City cleans major roads and commercial areas at night. Residential areas are swept during the day.</p><p>You can see when street sweeping is scheduled for your block on official signage. These signs list restricted times for parks. Please move your vehicle accordingly.</p><p>[insert picture of a parking sign as an example] [insert map that city is working on that shows what time street sweeping is on each street]</p>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '[]', NULL, 'information', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2015-12-19 00:00:22', '2016-03-01 18:36:04', 'f1b9f49f-3f6f-4aef-a305-53a3e3277c56'),
 ('302', '302', 'en_us', 'Disabled Person Parking', '', '<h2 id=\"disabled-person-parking-privileges\">Disabled Person Parking Privileges</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>People with disabilities and Disabled Veterans with a valid license plate or placard issued by the California DMV may park in the following areas:</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n  <li>\r\n    <p>In parking spaces with the International Symbol of Access (wheelchair symbol).</p>\r\n  </li>\r\n  <li>\r\n    <p>Next to a blue curb authorized for persons with disabilities parking.</p>\r\n  </li>\r\n  <li>Next to a green curb (green curbs indicate limited time parking) for as long as you wish. There is no time limit with a DP placard, DP license plates or DV license plates.</li>\r\n  <li>In an on-street metered parking space at no charge for as long as you wish. There is no time limit with a DP placard, DP license plates or DV license plates.</li>\r\n  <li>In an area that indicates it requires a resident or merchant permit for as long as you wish. There is no time limit with a DP placard, DP license plates or DV license plates.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<h2 id=\"disabled-person-parking-limitations\">Disabled Person Parking Limitations</h2>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<p>You may <strong>not park</strong>:</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n  <li>\r\n    <p>In spaces marked with a crosshatched pattern next to a parking space with the International Symbol of Access (wheelchair symbol). These spaces are for wheelchair and wheelchair lift access.</p>\r\n  </li>\r\n  <li>Next to red curbs, which indicate no stopping, standing or parking.</li>\r\n  <li>\r\n    <p>Next to yellow curbs, which are for commercial vehicles to load and unload passengers or freight.</p>\r\n  </li>\r\n  <li>Next to white curbs, which are for loading and unloading passengers or depositing mail in an adjacent mailbox.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<ul></ul>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<table>\r\n<thead>\r\n<tr><th>Parking Areas</th><th>Meaning</th></tr>\r\n</thead>\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr><td style=\"background-color:blue\"><strong>Handicapped symbol</strong></td><td>You can park in spaces with the International Symbol of Access</td></tr>\r\n<tr><td style=\"background-color:blue\"><strong>Blue</strong></td><td>This parking is reserved for persons with disabilities.</td></tr>\r\n<tr><td style=\"background-color:green\"><strong>Green</strong></td><td>You can park here as long as you want with a valid placard or license plate for the disabled.</td></tr>\r\n<tr><td style=\"background-color:white\"><strong>Parking Meter</strong></td><td>\r\nYou can park here as long as you want with a valid placard or license plate for the disabled. </td></tr>\r\n<tr><td style=\"background-color:white\"><strong>Resident and Merchant Permit Parking</strong></td><td>\r\nYou can park here as long as you want with a valid placard or license plate for the disabled. </td></tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<h2 id=\"disabled-person-parking-limitations-1\">Disabled Person Parking Limitations</h2>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<p>People with disabilities and Disabled Veterans with a valid license plate or placard issued by the California DMV may not park in the following areas:</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<table>\r\n<thead>\r\n<tr><th>Parking Areas</th><th>Meaning</th></tr>\r\n</thead>\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr><td style=\"background-color:white\"><strong>Crosshatched or Striped Areas</strong></td><td>\r\nYou can not park in spaces with a striped or crosshatched pattern.\r\n</td></tr>\r\n<tr><td style=\"background-color:red\"><strong>Red</strong></td><td>\r\nYou can not stop, idle or park your car.\r\n</td></tr>\r\n<tr><td style=\"background-color:yellow\"><strong>Yellow</strong></td><td>These areas are reserved for commercial vehicles.</td></tr>\r\n<tr><td style=\"background-color:white\"><strong>White</strong></td><td>These areas are reserved for picking up and dropping off passengers.\r\n</td></tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '[]', NULL, 'information', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2015-12-19 00:04:21', '2016-03-01 18:36:04', '30f5b603-80e1-4008-a72e-a1f5a6b67374'),
 ('312', '312', 'en_us', 'Apply for Disabled Persons Parking Placards and Plates', '', '<p>You may qualify for a Disabled Person placard or license plates if you have one or more of the conditions below.</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n  <li>Inability to use one or more lower limbs, or both hands</li>\r\n  <li>Diagnosed disease that impairs or interferes with mobility</li>\r\n  <li>Severe disability that leaves you unable to move without an assistive device</li>\r\n  <li>Documented problems with your eyesight such as lower-vision or partial-sightedness</li>\r\n  <li>The City of Oakland does not issue Disabled Person placards or license plates</li></ul>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<h3 id=\"illegal-use-of-disabled-parking\">Illegal Use of Disabled Parking</h3>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<p>Only the disabled driver issued the placard or plates can use the parking placard or plates.</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<p>A driver that does any of the actions below can receive tickets and fines.</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n  <li>Lend your Disabled Person placard to someone else</li>\r\n  <li>Use someone else’s Disabled Person placard</li>\r\n  <li>Have or display a fake Disabled Person placard or license plates</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<p>Report illegal use of Disabled Person placards and plates. Please call Parking Enforcement at (510) 238-3099.</p>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '[]', NULL, 'information', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2015-12-19 00:06:15', '2016-03-01 18:36:05', '9fba885b-3aba-4ece-90b6-c45f9f37e79d'),
