 ('632', '632', 'en_us', 'Oakland Encourages Residents and Businesses to Prepare for El Niño Storm Safety with “How To” Videos ', NULL, '<p><strong>Oakland, CA</strong> – The City of Oakland encourages residents and businesses to&nbsp;prepare for El Niño and strong winter storms. Three “how to” videos produced&nbsp;by the City provide quick, usable information about some specific, important&nbsp;steps to prepare for storms:</p>\r\n\r\n<ol><li>Building and using sandbags to protect against storm runoff and&nbsp;flooding</li><li>Using plastic sheeting as an additional barrier</li><li>Signing up for the City’s Adopt a Drain program to help prevent storm</li><li>Drain blockages and flooding</li></ol>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<p><a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/channel/UC4_la5PrP_f7f_PZPXo7D_w\">Watch and download videos on YouTube.</a></p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<p>We are asking&nbsp;the media to share and post these three public service announcements as part&nbsp;of your coverage of the winter weather.</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<p>El Niño is expected to bring winter storms significantly larger than normal, as&nbsp;well as the potential for flooding and other storm damage. Oaklanders need to&nbsp;work together to prepare and keep our city safe. It is vitally important that&nbsp;residents and businesses take steps to prepare for winter storms, and these&nbsp;videos show some effective steps.&nbsp;</p>', '2016-01-12 00:00:00', 'Oakland Encourages Residents and Businesses to Prepare for El Niño Storm Safety with “How To” Videos ', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '[]', NULL, 'info', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'hide', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p>Kristine Shaff<br>Public Information Officer<br>(510) 238-2966<br>kshaff@oaklandnet.com</p>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2016-01-19 02:53:41', '2016-03-01 18:36:07', 'a60d15d9-fc75-4429-86f3-4754e398ca79'),
 ('642', '642', 'en_us', 'Register for Weather Ready Workshops', 'Winter Ready Workshops Help Oaklanders Prepare for El Nino', '<p>Winter workshops&nbsp;highlight&nbsp;the preparation needed&nbsp;to keep your family, pets and property safe.&nbsp;Participants will learn important information and the steps to take to prepare for severe weather situations including heavy rains, flooding, high winds and power outages.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><b>Saturday, January 16, 2016, 10 a.m. to Noon</b><br>81st Avenue Library, 1021 81st&nbsp;Ave.&nbsp;<br>Workshop will be presented in English and Spanish. &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <a href=\"http://www2.oaklandnet.com/oakca1/groups/fire/documents/webcontent/oak056491.pdf\" target=\"true\">Download the workshop flyer.</a></p>\r\n\r\n<p><b>Wednesday, January 27, 2016, 6 to 8 p.m. &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; </b>Chabot Space & Science Center, 10000 Skyline Blvd. &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; Workshop will be presented in English. &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <a href=\"http://www2.oaklandnet.com/oakca1/groups/fire/documents/webcontent/oak056492.pdf\" target=\"true\">Download the workshop flyer.</a></p>\r\n\r\n<p>For a schedule of upcoming CORE workshops, <a href=\"http://www2.oaklandnet.com/oakca1/groups/fire/documents/webcontent/oak056303.pdf\" target=\"true\">download the schedule</a>.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Still have questions?&nbsp;</strong></p><ul><li>Call us at&nbsp;(510) 238-6351 &nbsp;</li><li>Email us at&nbsp;<a href=\"mailto:core@oaklandnet.com\">core@oaklandnet.com</a></li></ul>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '[]', NULL, 'info', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'hide', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2016-01-19 03:16:40', '2016-03-01 18:36:07', '3c333886-b5f2-4a93-ae63-74ff70735d71'),
 ('652', '652', 'en_us', 'Read the Latest Oakland Storm Reports', 'An Overview of Storm Related Service Requests & Reported Problems', '<p>The City of Oakland responds to thousands of requests to repair City infrastructure every year. Winter storms can often increase reports of drainage and sewer issues that impact community members. Additionally, the City continues to respond to issues on City buildings and offer support to the Oakland community. These issues and concerns&nbsp;are documented in City \'storm reports\' that are created at the end of a storm period.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>You can download PDF copies of storm reports for the following dates:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul><li><a href=\"http://www2.oaklandnet.com/oakca1/groups/pwa/documents/agenda/oak056633.pdf\" target=\"true\">Monday, January 11, 2016</a></li><li><a href=\"http://www2.oaklandnet.com/oakca1/groups/pwa/documents/report/oak056472.pdf\" target=\"true\">Monday, December 28, 2016</a></li><li><a href=\"http://www2.oaklandnet.com/oakca1/groups/pwa/documents/report/oak056403.pdf\" target=\"true\">Monday, December 21, 2016</a>.</li></ul>\r\n\r\n<p><br></p>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '[]', NULL, 'info', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'hide', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2016-01-19 05:14:38', '2016-03-01 18:36:07', '2f73a99a-4813-4a1d-bd60-1de325e1583d'),
 ('662', '662', 'en_us', 'Read El Nino Press Releases', 'Learn more about City-wide El Nino Preparation', '<p><strong>Oakland Press Releases & Presentations</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul><li>January 7, 2016:&nbsp;<a href=\"http://www2.oaklandnet.com/ElNino/OAK056596\"><strong>Oakland Offers El Nino Preparedness Workshops</strong></a></li><li>January 5, 2016:&nbsp;<a href=\"http://www2.oaklandnet.com/ElNino/OAK056594\"><strong>Presentation to Oakland City Council&nbsp;on Public Works&nbsp;El Niño Preparation</strong></a></li><li>December 22, 2015:&nbsp;<strong><a href=\"http://www2.oaklandnet.com/ElNino/OAK056422\">Three El Nino Safety \"How To\" Videos</a>\"</strong></li><li>December 9, 2015:<strong>&nbsp;</strong><a href=\"http://www2.oaklandnet.com/oakca1/groups/pwa/documents/pressrelease/oak056236.pdf\"><strong>Urging Residents & Businesses to Prepare&nbsp;for Winter Storms</strong></a></li></ul>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '[]', NULL, 'info', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'hide', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2016-01-19 05:19:22', '2016-03-01 18:36:07', 'd62f93c7-d3d5-4610-a2f2-4a8c2a22a77c'),
 ('672', '672', 'en_us', 'Preparation Tips & Tricks for Winter Storms', 'Prepare in Advance. Keep your family, pets and property safe.', '<p>Use this guide to prepare for severe weather situations<br>including heavy rains, flooding, high winds and power outages.<br>Follow these basic guidelines to prepare, respond and recover from<br>strong winter storms.</p><p><strong>For Your Family</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul><li>Be prepared for flooding, power outages and road closures</li><li>Watch this FEMA video:&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=LviZ4pZrqu8\">Family Communications Plan and Emergency Kit</a>&nbsp;&nbsp;</li><li>Make contingency plans for shelter should your home flood or become inaccessible</li><li>Discuss evacuation plans with your family now</li><li>Know emergency procedures and evacuation plans at your children\'s schools</li><li>Keep&nbsp;3-7 days of water, food, medicine and other supplies on hand for all family members and pets</li><li>Click on&nbsp;<a href=\"http://www.ready.gov/\">www.Ready.gov</a>&nbsp;for Family Plans, emergency kit lists, and so much more for you and yours!</li><li>Keep your pets safe and warm also, by&nbsp;<a href=\"http://www2.oaklandnet.com/Government/o/OFD/s/CORE/OAK026272\">preparing ahead of time with these tips</a>.</li></ul><strong>For Your Home</strong>\r\n\r\n<ul><li>Get flood insurance, now! It can take 30 days for policies to take effect</li><li><a href=\"http://www.ktvu.com/community/56230229-video\">Watch this video about flood insurance</a>, by Bay Area People</li><li>Watch this video:&nbsp;<a href=\"https://vimeo.com/147505317\">How to Create Sandbags</a></li><li><a href=\"https://www.floodsmart.gov/toolkits/flood/downloads/WestCoastRainySeason-OT2007.pdf\">FEMA\'s FloodSmart Tool Kit</a></li><li><a href=\"http://www.water.ca.gov/floodmgmt/docs/brochure_floodfightingathome.pdf\">How to Fight Flooding, by California Dept. of Water Resources</a></li><li>Know Your Flood Risk: Search your address&nbsp;at&nbsp;<a href=\"http://www.floodsmart.gov/floodsmart\">www.Floodsmart.gov</a></li><li>Check your roof, rain gutters and chimney for holes and clear debris</li><li>Inspect and clean drains around your home and its foundation</li><li>Make sure windows are watertight</li><li>If you rent, discuss any issues with the property manager</li><li>Place sandbags in flood-prone areas</li><li>Ensure outdoor lights are working</li><li>Check your fences, your gates and your driveway for sturdiness and&nbsp;clear debris</li><li>Clear your yard of debris</li><li>Secure patio furniture, garbage cans and other items that might move if flooded</li><li>Review your insurance and consider flood insurance.&nbsp;United&nbsp;Policy Holders&nbsp;Insurance&nbsp;has a helpful website at&nbsp;<a href=\"http://www.uphelp.org/\">www.uphelp.org</a>.&nbsp;</li></ul><p><a href=\"http://www2.oaklandnet.com/oakca1/groups/pwa/documents/agenda/oak056634.pdf\" target=\"true\">Download a copy of our \"Storm Ready\" brochure.</a></p><p><br></p>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '[]', NULL, 'info', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'hide', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2016-01-19 05:30:22', '2016-03-01 18:36:07', 'd1241635-f2b7-4ab8-aa20-1ff06f56f710'),
 ('682', '682', 'en_us', 'Adopt a City Storm Drain', 'Volunteer to Adopt a Storm Drain in Your Neighborhood', '<p>The City \"Adopt a drain\" program<strong>&nbsp;</strong>seeks volunteers to help keep storm drains clear of debris. By keeping storm drain inlets clear, you can help prevent flooding during storms.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Want to learn more?&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<p>Watch this Bay Area People&nbsp;<a href=\"http://www.ktvu.com/community/56230465-video\">video about the Adopt a Drain Program</a>.</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Still have questions?</strong></p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<p>Call:&nbsp;(510) 238-7630</p>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '[]', NULL, 'info', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'hide', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2016-01-19 05:35:44', '2016-03-01 18:36:07', '9fcccbc6-52d9-474a-b51b-d8ff4dd3b8da'),
 ('692', '692', 'en_us', 'Pick Up Sandbags & Plastic Sheeting for Your Neighborhood', 'The City of Oakland Offers Sandbags & Plastic Sheeting to Residents and Businesses', '<p>The City of Oakland will provide emergency sandbags and plastic sheeting when heavy rains are forecast. Each Oakland resident and business owner may pickup sandbags (up to 10)&nbsp;and plastic sheeting (up to 20 feet) at the following locations, as long as supplies last.&nbsp;Bring your ID to prove residency. Be prepared to fill your own if needed.<br>&nbsp;<br><strong>Municipal Service Center</strong>, 7101 Edgewater Drive<br>Monday – Friday, 8 a.m. – 4 p.m.<br>Saturday & Sunday, 8 a.m. – 4:30 p.m.<br>After Hours (at entry gate) 4:30 p.m. – 8 a.m.<br>&nbsp;<br><strong>Drainage Services Facility</strong>, 5921 Shepherd Canyon<br>Monday – Friday, 8 a.m. – 4 p.m.<br>After Hours (at entry gate) 4:30 p.m. – 8 a.m.</p><p><strong>Need more bags?&nbsp;</strong>You can pick up bags at your local hardware, garden or home improvement stores.&nbsp;</p><p><strong>Want to learn how to make a sandbag?</strong> <a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=MRylOmhwgX8\" target=\"true\">Watch this video.</a></p><p><strong>Want to learn how to use plastic sheeting?</strong> <a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=oKxRIr-qaV4\" target=\"true\">Watch this video.</a></p>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '[]', NULL, 'info', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'hide', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2016-01-19 05:40:46', '2016-03-01 18:36:08', '580cc4e3-f067-4edd-904a-2c9d9b30b3f1'),
 ('702', '702', 'en_us', 'News Articles & Other Resources', 'A Collection of Articles, Videos & Other Resources', '<ul><li><strong>Listen to this KQED broadcast:&nbsp;<a href=\"https://soundcloud.com/kqed/preparing-for-el-nino-will-drainage-systems-handle-the-deluge-of-rain\">Preparing for El Niño: Will Drainage Systems Handle the Deluge of Rain?</a></strong></li><li><strong>Bay Area People&nbsp;</strong><a href=\"http://www.ktvu.com/community/56230465-video\">video about the Adopt&nbsp;A Drain</a>&nbsp;Program&nbsp;<strong>or&nbsp;<a href=\"http://adoptadrainoakland.com/\">click here to volunteer</a>.</strong></li><li><strong>Tribune Newspaper December 9, 2015&nbsp;</strong><a href=\"http://www2.oaklandnet.com/ElNino/OAK056240\">Click here to read or download the pdf.</a>&nbsp;</li><li><strong>KRON 4 December 22, 2015</strong>&nbsp;Click on&nbsp;<a href=\"http://kron4.com/2015/12/23/el-nino-what-can-you-do-to-prepare/\">What you can do to prepare</a>.&nbsp;</li><li><a href=\"http://sanfrancisco.cbslocal.com/2015/08/17/5-things-you-should-do-now-to-prepare-for-a-strong-rainy-el-nino/\">5 Things You Should Do Now to Prepare</a></li><li>FEMA Video:&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=kXw1feTnkU4\">Severe Weather</a></li><li>FEMA Video:&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=XVpGJ_Xl__w&feature=youtu.be\">When The Sky Turns Gray</a>&nbsp;(Animated)</li><li><a href=\"http://www.ktvu.com/community/56229808-video\">Winter Weather Preparedness</a>, by Bay Area People</li><li>Watch this&nbsp;<a href=\"http://www.pge.com/en/safety/naturaldisaster/stormsoutagessafety/poweroutage/index.page\">PG&E video about how outages occur in stormy weather</a></li><li>Coastal Commission’s El Nino Resource website&nbsp;<a href=\"http://www.coastal.ca.gov/climate/extreme-weather/el-nino/\">http://www.coastal.ca.gov/climate/extreme-weather/el-nino/</a>&nbsp;includes preparedness checklists for cities, property owners, shoreline properties, etc.</li><li>Alameda County also has an excellent website for those wanting to learn more:<a href=\"http://www.acgov.org/pwa/info/elnino.htm\">http://www.acgov.org/pwa/info/elnino.htm</a></li><li>Click on this link for web article from&nbsp;<a href=\"http://oceanservice.noaa.gov/news/dec15/california-flooding.html\">NOAA about CA Tides and Flooding</a></li></ul>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '[]', NULL, 'info', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'hide', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2016-01-19 05:42:46', '2016-03-01 18:36:08', 'dc88b98c-279b-4de4-9dd6-9763bdb1925d'),
