 ('1112', '932', 'en_us', 'Check Your Location with Utility Companies', '', '<h2>Local Utility&nbsp;Providers</h2><ul><li><a href=\"http://www.pge.com/\">PG&E</a> (Electricity and Gas)</li><li><a href=\"http://www.ebmud.com/\">EBMUD</a> (Water and Sewage)</li><li><a href=\"https://www.acgov.org/aceh/\">Alameda Country Environmental Health</a></li><li><a href=\"http://www.xfinity.com/\">Comcast</a> (Internet)</li></ul><p> Make sure to contact your utility providers&nbsp;as soon as you find your location to get everything&nbsp;in order.&nbsp; Depending on the services you need, your building may require&nbsp;upgrades which take additional time and money.&nbsp;It is recommended that you get your requests in early.</p>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '[]', NULL, 'info', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'hide', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2016-01-27 22:25:39', '2016-03-01 18:36:09', '6ad12bcd-60d6-4177-9031-3401c97c4045'),
 ('1122', '942', 'en_us', 'Register Your Business Name', 'File a fictitious business name statement', '<p>If you intend to name your firm anything other than your own name, you must file a Fictitious Business Name Statement at the Alameda County Clerk\'s Office.&nbsp;This generally costs $30.&nbsp;You can download an application online (PDF), pick one up in person, or have one mailed to you.</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<p>You may pay by cash, debit/ATM, check (personal, company, bank, cashier\'s or traveler\'s) or money order.</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<h4>Ficitious Business Name Applications & Info Hours</h4>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<p>Monday - Friday<br>8:30 am - 4:30 pm</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<h4>Turning in Your Application by Mail</h4>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<p>Please be sure to send the original and&nbsp;3 copies&nbsp;of the form and a self-addressed stamped envelope to ensure a prompt return of your copies. Payment for additional certified copies are $2.00 per copy.&nbsp;\r\nYou may pay by check (personal, company, bank, or cashiers), money order or traveler\'s checks. Out of country payments must be made in U.S. dollars. Credit cards are&nbsp;notaccepted for mail orders.</p>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '[]', NULL, 'info', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'hide', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2016-01-27 22:35:48', '2016-03-01 18:36:09', '46e23a07-b9ae-48fe-bd99-997795f39831'),
 ('1132', '952', 'en_us', 'Obtain Your Business Tax Certificate', 'To conduct any business in Oakland you must first obtain a Business Tax Certificate and pay an annual business tax', '<p>Before you start, you will need your <a href=\"{entry:872:url}\">Zoning Clearance</a> and <a href=\"{entry:942:url}\">Fictitious Business Name</a> applications approved.&nbsp;For more detail on&nbsp;exceptions on who needs a business tax certificate, click&nbsp;<a href=\"{entry:2:url}\"></a><a href=\"{entry:1082:url}\">here</a>.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Cost</h3>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<p>The $88&nbsp;registration fee must be paid and filed within 30 days of starting your business.&nbsp; If you file your registration later than 30 days after you start your business, you will need to pay a small penalty plus interest for each month beyond the 30 days.</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<h3>Application Process</h3>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<p>The New Business&nbsp;Application is available online&nbsp;and at our offices.&nbsp;You can pay by&nbsp;cash, check, cashier\'s check, money order,&nbsp;credit cards (Mastercard, Visa, & Discover),&nbsp;and ATM debit cards.&nbsp;However, if paying with an&nbsp;ATM&nbsp;debit card you must come into the office.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<p>The application can&nbsp;be returned by fax (with a&nbsp;credit card), via mail or in person. If submitting by fax, you may pay by phone by&nbsp;provide the social security number or federal tax identification number on record.&nbsp;You will get a paper certificate from the business tax office approximately two weeks after you pay your fee.</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<h3>Business Tax Office Hours</h3>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<p>Monday,&nbsp;Tuesday, Thursday, Friday&nbsp;8&nbsp;a.m.&nbsp;–&nbsp;4:00 p.m<br>Wednesday, 9:30 a.m. – 4:00 p.m</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<h3>Renewal</h3>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<p>Business taxes must be paid annually, on or before March 1st of each year. It is your responsibility to renew your certificate on time and/or to notify the Business Tax Office if you have not received your annual renewal declaration(s).</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<hr>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<h3>Non-Profit Registation</h3>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<p>All non-profit organizations located or doing business in the City of Oakland are required to register with the city. To register as a non-profit, you must first have your 501(c)(3) from the&nbsp;<a href=\"http://www.irs.gov/Charities-&-Non-Profits\">IRS</a>, the Letter of Exemption from the&nbsp;<a href=\"http://www.boe.ca.gov/info/VirtualSeminars/nonprofit_resources.html\">California State Franchise Board</a>, a copy of your Articles of Incorporation, and, if you have a location in the City of Oakland, a zoning clearance for your business location (please contact the&nbsp;<u><a href=\"http://www2.oaklandnet.com/Government/o/PBN/OurOrganization/PlanningZoning/o/Zoning/index.htm\">Zoning Division</a></u>&nbsp;to obtain zoning clearance).&nbsp;Once you have obtained the above documents you must complete a&nbsp;<a href=\"http://www.oaklandnet.com/government/fwawebsite/revenue/revenue_newbiaapp.htm\">Business Registration Application</a>&nbsp;and provide the City with copies of your 501(c)(3), Letter of Exemption, and Articles of Incorporation.</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<h3>More Info</h3>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<p>Get the&nbsp;<a href=\"http://www.oaklandnet.com/government/fwawebsite/revenue/revenue_biztax.htm\">business application (PDF), business tax classification and rate table, additional&nbsp;information, and FAQs</a>&nbsp;on the City\'s Finance and Management Agency website.<br></p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<p>Businesses located in or operating in Oakland need to pay an annual business tax on or before March 1 of each year.&nbsp;&nbsp;<a href=\"http://oaklandbusinesscenter.com/index.php?option=com_content&task=view&id=37&Itemid=50\">See more details on the annual business tax here.</a><br>&nbsp;<br><a href=\"http://oaklandbusinesscenter.com/index.php?option=com_content&task=view&id=102&Itemid=85\">Visit the BAC or request help from the BAC online</a>&nbsp;if you have additional questions or need more information.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<table><tbody><tr></tr></tbody></table>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '[]', NULL, 'info', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'hide', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2016-01-27 22:44:17', '2016-03-01 18:36:09', '1efe0659-c386-45ae-9b19-07c6de74c2a5'),
 ('1142', '962', 'en_us', 'Get your Tax and Employer ID Numbers', 'This is required if you will have employees', '<p>If you will have employees, obtain your Employer Identification Numbers<br></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Federal Taxpayer Identification Number<br>Internal Revenue Service<br>800.829.1040<br><a href=\"http://www.irs.gov/Businesses/Small-Businesses-&-Self-Employed/Apply-for-an-Employer-Identification-Number-%28EIN%29-Online\">www.irs.gov</a></p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<p>State Employer Identification Number<br>Employment Tax Office 916.654.7041<br><a href=\"http://www.edd.cahwnet.gov/taxreg.htm\">www.edd.cahwnet.gov/taxreg.htm</a></p>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '[]', NULL, 'info', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'hide', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2016-01-27 22:47:49', '2016-03-01 18:36:10', '6ecca961-fcc2-466c-9465-c2211310b2b6'),
 ('1152', '972', 'en_us', 'Get a Business Checking Account', 'Separate business and personal accounting is essential when you file your tax return, and it can save you money in the long run.', '<h2>Choosing the Right Bank & Establishing a Relationship</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>As a local business owner, you will want to open an account at a bank that is friendly to small businesses. Find a bank that shows a commitment to small businesses, and lends to local small businesses, because there is a good chance you will need a business loan to help you grow eventually.&nbsp; Establishing a good relationship with your bank early on will be a huge help when you ask for a line of credit or a loan later.&nbsp; Read the SBA article on&nbsp;<a href=\"http://www.sba.gov/smallbusinessplanner/start/financestartup/SERV_BANKERFRIEND.html\">The Benefits of Making Your Banker Your Friend</a>&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<h2>Finding Local Banks</h2>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<ul><li><a href=\"http://www.icba.org/consumer/BankLocator.cfm?sn.ItemNumber=51757\">Community Banks</a>&nbsp;</li><li><a href=\"http://www.cdfifund.gov/docs/certification/cdfi/CDFIbyState.pdf\">Community Development Institutions</a>&nbsp;(PDF - includes some non-bank institutions)</li><li><a href=\"http://www.ncua.gov/DataServices/FindCU.aspx\">Credit Unions</a>&nbsp;</li><li><a href=\"http://www2.fdic.gov/idasp/main_bankfind.asp\">All FDIC Insured Banks</a>&nbsp;(includes community and traditional, but not credit unions)</li></ul>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<h2>Types of banks</h2>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<p>There are many banks to choose from in Oakland and the Bay Area, and many of them serve small businesses. To help you understand the difference between the various types of banks, we offer a brief description of the major types:</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<h3>Community Bank</h3>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<p>Community banks are locally-owned and operated banks that offer all of the standard services of other banks but with a focus on the serving the specific needs of the local community. Some community banks may be focused on mortgage lending, others on small business, etc. Loans are primarily given to people and businesses in the local area, helping to build the local economy.&nbsp; Learn more from the<a href=\"http://www.icba.org/\">Independent Community Bankers Association</a></p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<h3>Community Development Bank</h3>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<p>Community Development banks provide capital to help economically distressed communities through targeted lending and investing.&nbsp; Like community banks, they are locally focused, while also serving specifically low-income and underserved individuals and neighborhoods.&nbsp; Learn from from the&nbsp;<a href=\"http://communitydevelopmentbanks.org/\">Community Development Bankers Association</a><strong><br></strong></p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<h3>Credit Union</h3>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<p>A Credit Union is a non-profit financial cooperative, owned exclusively by its members, designed to pool savings so that members can get loans at a reasonable rate. Credit unions are often locally focused because their memberships are usually based on where people live or work. Credit unions are often more focused on consumer loans rather than business loans. For more information, check out the&nbsp;<a href=\"http://www.ncua.gov/\">National Credit Union Administration</a><strong><br></strong></p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<h3>Traditional Commercial Banks&nbsp;</h3>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<p>Traditional commercial banks are institutions for the purpose of making profits for their owners and shareholders.&nbsp; As banks continue to merge, the remaining banks become larger and have a larger geographic footprint, from local to national to international. To learn more about banks in general, check out this&nbsp; Banking Basics document from the&nbsp;<a href=\"http://www.bos.frb.org/education/pubs/bankingbasics.htm\">Boston Federal Reserve</a>.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<p>Alternative lenders are focused on strengthening the local economy and creating jobs in the community; this mission means that they will spend more time looking at aspects of a business beyond credit scores that can help show that a business is a good candidate for a loan.</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<h2>Documentation required</h2>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<p>In order to obtain a bank account you will usually need the following: &nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<p>•&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Business Tax ID #</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<p>•&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Business name filing document, such as a Fictitious Name Certificate&nbsp;<br>•&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Organizing document, such as Articles of Incorporation (if available) or bylaws<br>•&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Corporate Resolution identifying authorized signers if officer names are not listed on&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<h2>Articles of Association or bylaws</h2>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<p>It is also in the best interest of the business that two signers are required to open the account and to sign checks.<br></p>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '[]', NULL, 'info', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'hide', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2016-01-27 22:52:03', '2016-03-01 18:36:10', '48d0df62-565b-473c-b683-fd4ce3c9f464'),
 ('1162', '982', 'en_us', 'Schedule Your Building Inspections', '', '<h3>Building Services Hours</h3>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<p>Hours: Monday, Tuesday, Thursday, Friday 8:00a.m.- 4:00p.m&nbsp;and&nbsp;Wednesday 9:30a.m. - 4:00p.m.</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<p>The Building Services inspections include ADA compliance&nbsp;mechanical, electrical, and plumbing inspections.&nbsp;It is your responsibility to schedule all inspections and ensure your business stays up to date with all the latest regulations.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Inspections are required to insure that the construction is proceeding according to the approved plans and project conditions-of-approval, and that all current code standards are being met.</p><p>An appointment must be made at least one working day in advance, and during busy construction months they may take several days to schedule.&nbsp;Periodic inspections must be scheduled until the project is completed and the City gives final approval.&nbsp;After the job has received a final inspection, the building permit will be kept on file in the Building Services Department as proof of the work completed.</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<p><strong>During the construction phase, inspections by City Inspectors are required prior to:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<ul><li>Placing concrete or grout;</li><li>Covering electrical, plumbing, or mechanical work;</li><li>Covering floor framing;</li><li>Covering interior sides of wall framing;</li><li>Taping gypsum wallboard;</li><li>Applying stucco;</li><li>Insulation;</li><li>Shower Walls prior to tiling;</li><li>Exterior & Interior shear nailing;</li><li>Waterproof membrane at exterior balconies, stairs etc;</li><li>Roof plywood nailing;</li><li>Roof framing;</li><li>Shafts;</li><li>Fire protection</li></ul>\r\n\r\n<p><br><strong>Inspections are also required prior to connecting to, or the hook-up of:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul><li>Gas lines;</li><li>Electrical service; and/or</li><li>Water and sewer services.</li></ul>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<p><br></p>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '[]', NULL, 'info', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'hide', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2016-01-27 22:53:50', '2016-03-01 18:36:10', '45d6b6ea-9805-4ad4-8fa3-6c2194632975'),
 ('1172', '992', 'en_us', 'Apply for Business Permits', 'Learn more about the permits, fees, and other governmental requirements for businesses to legally operate', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '[]', NULL, 'info', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'hide', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2016-01-27 22:56:30', '2016-03-01 18:36:10', '93418709-72c2-4173-8e92-e58023e5266d'),
 ('1182', '1002', 'en_us', 'Search Permits by Business Types', '', '<p>CalGold is a state-operated website that provides a list of the regional, state, and federal licenses and permits required for businesses in each California city.</p>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '[]', NULL, 'info', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'hide', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2016-01-27 23:04:31', '2016-03-01 18:36:10', '7133f78e-b4fa-4d5f-8a3a-e03d1491d660'),
 ('1192', '1012', 'en_us', 'Common Permit Types', 'Learn more about permits that are required by common business types', '<p>The following are standard permits required for common types of businesses. However, this is not a complete list for all types of businesses.&nbsp; Make sure to check CalGold website to get the permits needed for your type of business, as described at the bottom of this page.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>City of Oakland Requirements</h2>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<h3>Building Permits</h3>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<p>Building permits are documents which are obtained through the Office of Planning and Building authorizing the start of construction or remodeling of a building in the City of Oakland. There are four types of permits which may be required:&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<ol><li>Building</li><li>Electrical</li><li>Plumbing</li><li>Mechanical</li></ol>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<p><a href=\"http://www.oaklandnet.com/government/ceda/revised/building_permits.html\">Get more details from Building Services</a></p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<h3>Rent Adjustment</h3>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<p>If you rent out one or more residential units, you may be subject to the City of Oakland’s Rent Program service fee of $30 per year per unit.</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<p><a href=\"http://cedaonline.oaklandnet.com/rentadjustmentsite/index.htm\">Get details here</a></p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<h3>Excess Litter Fee</h3>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<p>If you are operating one of the types of businesses below, you may be subject to the Excess Litter Fee.</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<ul><li>Fast food restaurants\r\n\r\n</li><li>Convenience markets\r\n\r\n</li><li>Gasoline station markets\r\n\r\n</li><li>Liquor stores&nbsp;</li></ul>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<p><a href=\"http://www.oaklandnet.com/documents/WEBPAGEELF92206.pdf\">Get more details in this PDF file</a></p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<h3>Peddler/Solicitor Permit</h3>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<p>If you intend to sell or solicit door-to-door, you must obtain a peddler permit.&nbsp; Obtain the permit application at:</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<p>Oakland Police Department<br>455 7th Street, Room 306<br>Oakland, 94607.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<p>Bring the completed Peddler Permit to the Business Tax office.</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<h3>Fire Department Permits</h3>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<p>If you are starting a new business, or are expanding an existing business in Oakland which includes the operation, and/or storage and/or manufacturing of a wide variety of items, you are required to submit a permit application to the Fire Prevention Office. Your application will be reviewed, an inspection of your business will be conducted, and a determination will be made as to the issuance of the permit.</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Important note: Business owners are advised to&nbsp;</strong><strong>meet with the Oakland Fire Department early on</strong>&nbsp;in your planning stage, as many permits are rejected annually due to wrong use code and other issues found during the inspection phase. Meeting with the Oakland Fire Department from the onset will save you time and money as you are starting or expanding your business. Don\'t assume that your business doesn\'t apply!</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<p><a href=\"http://www.oaklandnet.com/fire/fpb/\">Get more details from the Fire Prevention Office</a>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<h2>County and State&nbsp;Requirements</h2>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<h3>Fictitious Business Name</h3>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<p>You must register your business name with the Alameda County Clerk-Recorder\'s Office.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<p><a href=\"http://www.acgov.org/auditor/clerk/filefbn1.htm\">More details from Alameda County Clerk-Recorder\'s Office</a></p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<h3>Retail/Wholesale Sales</h3>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<p>If you will be selling retail or wholesale items which require collection of state sales taxes, you need a Sellers Permit.</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<p><a href=\"http://www.boe.ca.gov/\">More details from California State Board of Equalization</a></p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<h3>Food Establishments</h3>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<p>If you will be serving and selling food, you must obtain a health permit before applying for your Business Tax Certificate.</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<p><a href=\"http://www.acgov.org/aceh/\">More details from Alameda County Environmental Health</a></p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<h3>Alcoholic Beverage Sales</h3>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<p>If you intend to sell alcoholic beverages, you must have an Alcoholic Beverage License.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<p><a href=\"http://www.abc.ca.gov/\">More details from California state Alcoholic Beverage Control</a></p><h3>Hazardous Waste</h3><p>If your company intends to deal with hazardous waste&nbsp;(such as solvents, motor oil, paints, pesticides, fertilizers,&nbsp;aerosol, etc), you will need to apply for a hazardous waste permit with the County of Alameda.</p><p>For more details, call&nbsp;Alameda County Environmental Health at 1&nbsp;(510) 567-6702 or visit their <a href=\"https://www.acgov.org/aceh/\">website</a>.</p>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '[]', NULL, 'info', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'hide', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2016-01-27 23:10:58', '2016-03-01 18:36:10', '17d7a837-50a3-4e95-a324-2299c5c2291d'),
 ('1202', '1022', 'en_us', 'Recruit and Train Employees', '', '<p>There are several organizations, government agencies, and online materials to help you find, hire, and manage employees.&nbsp;&nbsp;Check out the&nbsp;<a href=\"http://oaklandbusinesscenter.com/index.php?option=com_content&task=view&id=47&Itemid=53\">Employees&nbsp;</a>section of this site for more information.</p>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '[]', NULL, 'info', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'hide', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2016-01-27 23:17:26', '2016-03-01 18:36:10', 'c572876f-a897-4ad6-bf2b-fe630742838e'),
 ('1212', '1032', 'en_us', 'Green your Business', 'Local resources to help businesses learn how to go green, get certified, and network with other green businesses.', '<h2>Getting Certified</h2>\r\n\r\n<h3>Alameda County Green Business Program</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>The Alameda County Green Business Program offers certification for&nbsp; businesses that can demonstrate that they practice resource conservation (water and energy) and pollution prevention (toxics reduction). In addition to recognizing businesses for their green practices, Certified Green Businesses can use the highly recognizable logo on their advertising and are able to network with other Green Businesses.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><a href=\"http://www.greenbiz.ca.gov/AboutUsAC.html\">Green Business Information & Application</a></p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Green America (formerly Co-Op America)</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Green America’s mission is to harness economic power&mdash;the strength of consumers, businesses and the marketplace&mdash;to create a socially just and environmentally sustainable society. Green America helps consumers find socially- and environmentally-responsible businesses.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><a href=\"http://www.greenamericatoday.org/cabn/join/index.cfm\">Click here to learn more and join Green America.</a><br>&nbsp;<br></p>\r\n\r\n<h2>Resources for Greening Your Business</h2>\r\n\r\n<h3>Business Recycling and Waste Reduction in Oakland</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Check the StopWaste.org website for comprehensive information on recycling, composting, reuse, and waste reduction.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><a href=\"http://stopwaste.org/\">StopWaste.org</a></p>\r\n\r\n<h3>East Bay Energy Watch</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>PG&E, the cities of Oakland and Berkeley, the counties of Alameda and Contra Costa are working together on the East Bay Energy Watch (EBEW). BEW promotes reduced energy use and energy savings targets by providing energy efficiency information and direct installation of energy efficient&nbsp;equipment to eligible PG&E customers including lighting, refrigeration, building heating and cooling and other energy systems used by businesses.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><a href=\"http://www.pge.com/ebep\">www.pge.com/ebep</a></p>\r\n\r\n<h3>City of Oakland Green Business Projects</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>The City has a department dedicated to green business projects and resources.&nbsp; For the latest resources, contact the Business Assistance Center.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Classes</h3>\r\n\r\n<p><a href=\"http://oaklandbusinesscenter.com/index.php?option=com_mtree&task=advsearch2&search_id=61&Itemid=82\">See a list of organizations that provide green business classes&nbsp;</a></p>\r\n\r\n<h2>Promoting and Networking with Other Green Businesses</h2>\r\n\r\n<p><a href=\"http://www.sustainablebiz.org/\">Sustainable Business Alliance</a>&nbsp;<br>Based in Berkeley, the Sustainable Business Alliance is a membership organization for Bay Area companies committed to greater environmental and socially responsible business practices.&nbsp; Workshops and networking events every month!</p>\r\n\r\n<p><a href=\"http://greenchamberofcommerce.net/\">Green Chamber of Commerce</a>&nbsp;<br>The Green Chamber of Commerce is dedicated to fostering the success of businesses committed to environmental and social responsibility. Based in the Bay Area, the Green Chamber is working to build chapters across the country.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><a href=\"http://www.greenbiz.ca.gov/ShopGreen.html\">Certified Green Businesses</a><br>As mentioned above, Alameda County certifies green businesses.&nbsp; When you become certified, you join a network of other green businesses, and will be invited to green businesses events.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<table><tbody><tr>\r\n</tr></tbody></table>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '[]', NULL, 'info', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'hide', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2016-01-29 23:26:05', '2016-03-01 18:36:11', '9c07485a-9928-4b85-879c-652272e7b1fd'),
 ('1222', '1042', 'en_us', 'Connect with Local Business Communities and Advisors', 'Local organizations to join to grow your network and get advice for your business', '<p>Businesses of all stages and sizes can benefit from advisors and programs to help them build smart strategies for long term survival and growth. Here are some resources to help you out.</p><h4>Sustainable Business Alliance</h4>\r\n\r\n<p><a href=\"http://sustainablebusinessalliance.org\">Sustainable Business Alliance</a></p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<p>A business association committed to building a vibrant community of locally-owned, sustainably-minded businesses in the East Bay.&nbsp;<br></p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<ul><li>Providing our members with opportunities for networking, business development, and learning best practices for operating sustainably.</li><li>Educating the public on the benefits of local living economies and encouraging residents and businesses to spend locally.</li><li>Supporting public policy changes that advance sustainable economic development, through our affiliation with the American Sustainable Business Council.</li></ul>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<h4>Oakland Grown</h4>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<p><a href=\"http://www.oaklandgrown.org/\">www.oaklandgrown.org</a></p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<p>Our vision includes the creation of a permanent local network that:<br></p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<ul><li>Supports the growth and development of locally owned and independently operated businesses and local artists in Oakland</li><li>Encourages local purchasing by residents, businesses, and artists</li><li>Creates opportunities for business owners and artists to network and share best practices</li><li>Advocates for public policies that strengthen independent local businesses and artists, and helps level the economic playing field.</li></ul>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<h4>Alameda County Small Business Development Center</h4>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<p><a href=\"http://oaklandbusinesscenter.com/index.php?option=com_mtree&task=visit&link_id=9&Itemid=82\">www.acsbdc.org</a><br></p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<ul><li>Expert consulting, top-notch seminars, linkages to other resource providers and business planning services to business owners interested in accelerating the success of their ventures.</li><li>Consulting is free, and most workshops are also free.&nbsp;Our team of Business Advisors come from a variety of high-growth industries and corporate backgrounds and work hands-on with clients to address challenges and seize opportunities.</li></ul>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<h4>Business Value Alliance</h4>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<p>www.<a href=\"http://oaklandbusinesscenter.com/index.php?option=com_mtree&task=visit&link_id=42&Itemid=82\">businessvaluealliance.net</a></p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<ul><li>BVA equips motivated owners with practical methods, tools and strategic business tools to improve business performance and grow for the long-term.&nbsp;</li><li>BVA offers several programs and services, including: a variety of workshops, a 9-month group program called Created in Oakland, a Business Growth Design Studio, and custom one-on-one advising on business growth.</li></ul>\r\n\r\n<h4>Inner City Advisors</h4>\r\n\r\n<p><a href=\"http://www.innercityadvisors.org\">www.innercityadvisors.org</a></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Inner City Advisors (ICA) helps build sustainable and responsible inner city businesses that create quality jobs, reinvest in the community and contribute to the local economy. We accomplish our mission by providing our Portfolio Companies and other local entrepreneurs with&nbsp;high caliber consulting, strategic advice, entrepreneurship education and access to resources and professional networks.</p>\r\n\r\n<h4>Renaissance Entrepreneurship Center</h4>\r\n\r\n<p><a href=\"http://www.rencenter.org\">www.rencenter.org</a></p>\r\n\r\n<p>The mission of Renaissance Entrepreneurship Center is to empower and increase the entrepreneurial capacities of socially and economically diverse women and men, and thereby strengthen our communities through the creation of sustainable new businesses, new jobs, and the promotion of financial self-sufficiency.<br></p>\r\n\r\n<h4>Urban FIRE</h4>\r\n\r\n<p><a href=\"http://www.urbanfire.org\">www.urbanfire.org</a></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Urban FIRE (Financial Intelligence, Responsible Entrepreneurship) is training to start and sustain a micro-business based on a proven, real world experiential system. Ignite your passion, burn the status quo and light a path to self determination. Our brand of entrepreneurship is about your personal success, business as a \"B Corp\"(<a href=\"http://www.bcorporation.net),social\">www.bcorporation.net)</a>, social&nbsp;justice and building our local economy - because we all live in an intradependent urban society. Urban FIRE meets weekly for three hours for 24 weeks divided into two semesters. There is no greater purpose than launching the genius that lies within you and creating a rewarding business that speaks to your soul. Urban FIRE Entrepreneurship is more than just about business, it\'s about building a successful life. We partner with Oakland Adult and Career Education to offer our classes at a price affordable to everyone.<br></p>\r\n\r\n<hr>\r\n\r\n<p>For an advanced search of additional organizations click <a href=\"http://oaklandbusinesscenter.com/index.php?option=com_mtree&task=advsearch\">here.</a>&nbsp;</p>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '[]', NULL, 'info', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'hide', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2016-02-01 22:13:38', '2016-03-01 18:36:11', '31f16c1a-a93d-4c23-9e50-e33c648cda08'),
 ('1232', '1052', 'en_us', 'Get Consultation on What Permits You Will Need', '', '<p>Figuring out what permits you may need for your business can be a complicated process. We recommend talking to a business permitting specialist either in person or on the phone. Some permits can be easily approved over the counter&nbsp;while others may take additional time based on factors such as exterior&nbsp;designs, late night hours, or parking.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Visit or Call Us</h3>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<p>Oakland Business Assistance Center<br>270 Frank H. Ogawa Plaza<br>1&nbsp;(510)&nbsp;238-7952<br>Monday – Friday&nbsp;<br>9:00 a.m. – 5:00 p.m.</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<h3>Talk with a Specialist</h3>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Keira Williams<br></strong><em>Retail</em><br>(510) 238-3853<br><a href=\"mailto:kwilliams@oaklandnet.com\">kwilliams@oaklandnet.com</a></p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Marisa Raya</strong><br><em>Technology</em><br>(510) 238-6230&nbsp;<br><a href=\"mailto:mraya@oaklandnet.com\">mraya@oaklandnet.com</a></p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Steve Lautze</strong><br><em>Green, Recycle-based, or Alternative Energy</em><br>(510) 238-4973<br><a href=\"mailto:slautze@oaklandnet.com\">slautze@oaklandnet.com</a></p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Margot Lederer Prado</strong><br><em>Manufacturing and Industrial Uses, Arts/Engineering/Design, Food and Beverage, Healthcare and Wellness</em><br>(510) 238-6766 &nbsp;&nbsp;<br><a href=\"mailto:mprado@oaklandnet.com\">mprado@oaklandnet.com</a></p>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '[]', NULL, 'info', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'hide', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2016-02-04 00:09:53', '2016-03-01 18:36:11', '08275529-138c-47a6-bfe7-7a367aa8910f'),
