 ('1252', '1072', 'en_us', 'Launching and Marketing Your Business', 'The City provides a variety of services to help you market your business', '<p>There are a variety of marketing services and opportunities available to Oakland businesses.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Get Grand Opening Assistance</h3>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<p>The City of Oakland\'s Marketing department helps new businesses with press releases and events to announce their new businesses.&nbsp; Contact the Public Information Officer at 1&nbsp;(510)&nbsp;238-2107.</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<h3>Oakland Grown</h3>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<p>The Oakland Grown campaign is Oakland’s campaign to encourage people to support locally-owned businesses and artists when they shop.&nbsp; Oakland businesses and artists that are locally-based and independently owned can get decals, listings on the Shop Oakland Grown website and other marketing benefits.&nbsp; Learn more on the&nbsp;<a href=\"http://oaklandgrown.org/join.php\">Oakland Grown website</a>.</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<h3>Marketing Green Businesses</h3>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<p>Certified Green Businesses take advantage of the decals, website listings and other marketing that the Alameda County Green Business program does to promote green businesses. To become a green business and benefit from these marketing benefits, check out the&nbsp;<a href=\"http://www.greenbiz.ca.gov/ShopGreenAC.html#legal\">Alameda County Green Business website</a>. &nbsp; &nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<p><br></p>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '[]', NULL, 'info', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'hide', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2016-02-05 23:34:36', '2016-03-01 18:36:11', '5118381d-fd5b-4356-961b-7b0e493fb513'),
 ('1262', '1082', 'en_us', 'Confirm if you Need to Register your Business', '', '<p><strong>Who is required to pay business tax?</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Anyone who conducts business or owns rental property in the City of Oakland (residential, commercial and industrial) are required to file and pay an annual business tax.&nbsp;<br></p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<p>If your business is located <em>outside</em> of the City of Oakland, but doing business <em>within </em>the city, you have to pay for the&nbsp;business tax certificate.</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<p>If your business is located <em>with</em><em>in</em>&nbsp;the City of Oakland, but does business <em>outside</em> the city, you have to pay for the business tax certificate. However, you may apportion your gross receipts. Apportionment Guidelines are available under Director of Finance Tax Rulings 7, 8, 9 or 10.&nbsp;<a href=\"http://www.oaklandnet.com/government/fwawebsite/revenue/revenue_taxrulings.htm\"></a><a href=\"http://www.oaklandnet.com/government/fwawebsite/revenue/revenue_taxrulings.htm\">Click here</a>.</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Non-Profits:</strong>&nbsp;If you are a non-profit Federal or State of California tax-exempt organization, you may be exempt from payment of the business tax. You must submit a copy of your letter of determination from the Internal Revenue Service or from the California Franchise Tax Board confirming the exemption from income tax. However you are required to register and pay the registration fee.</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Renting property:</strong>&nbsp;All property owners in Oakland who wish to rent out their property must file and pay the initial $88.00 Registration Fee to obtain a business tax certificate. The tax is based on annual gross rental income at a rate of $13.95 per $1,000 of gross rental income. If the property is residential or mixed use, you must also complete the New Rent Adjustment Program Fee Application (RAP). If the property is 100% commercial/industrial, it is not necessary to complete this (RAP) application.</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Renting a room:&nbsp;</strong>All persons who rent or sublet rooms must obtain a business tax certificate. The tax is based gross rental income at a rate of $13.95 per $1,000 of gross rental income.</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<p><br></p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<p><br></p>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '[]', NULL, 'info', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'hide', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2016-02-08 19:08:02', '2016-03-01 18:36:12', '3f162460-2987-43aa-90b6-2c82aac83c57');
