 ('1552', '1712', 'en_us', 'Check Zoning Regulations for Your Property', '', '<p>Once you have a couple of location options, you should check&nbsp;the planning map and zoning code&nbsp;to see if your location outright permitted, conditionally permitted or not permitted.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>This step can be complicated depending on the type of business. Unless you are familiar with planning and zoning regulations, we recommend you talk with a planner at the City of&nbsp;Oakland.</p>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '[]', NULL, 'info', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'hide', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2016-02-10 23:20:08', '2016-03-01 18:36:13', '7a241ded-d1fe-4cb7-9724-d8d00f588f0d'),
 ('1562', '1752', 'en_us', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '[]', NULL, 'info', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'hide', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'The best place to find official services and information from the City of Oakland.', 'oakland city government service information business parking jobs careers emergency news departments permits ', '[{\"col1\":\"business\",\"col2\":\"longfellow-rose\"},{\"col1\":\"parking\",\"col2\":\"water-blue\"}]', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2016-02-10 23:35:34', '2016-02-12 00:54:16', '87040ad6-94f0-4a23-bdd4-6857563d49cd'),
 ('1572', '1782', 'en_us', 'Schedule an Inspection with the Fire Prevention Bureau', '', '<p>The Commercial Inspection Program mandates that annual inspections of all commercial facilities and multi-family residences (apartments, hotels, motels, etc.) be conducted as designated by the State of California Health and Safety Code, and City of Oakland ordinance. These annual field inspections, that are managed and directed by the Fire Prevention Bureau, are conducted by the members of the OFD Operations Division annually, on a block-by-block basis, with the intent to inspect all commercial & residential properties as it pertains to the code and ordinance; provide fire and other life safety hazards education to business owners/occupants; and conduct pre-fire planning for future emergency response. The only properties exempt from said inspections are single-family dwellings and duplex buildings.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Commercial inspections are conducted as time permits during a fire station’s 24-hour shift and are not routinely scheduled on an appointment basis. &nbsp;As a general rule, if an inspection was conducted last year, business owners/occupants should receive an inspection within 30 days before or after the previous years’ inspection. Additionally, if there are no guarantees that an inspection will be completed due to fire department emergency response needs.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>This is an excellent program that provides fire safety personnel an opportunity to meet business owners/occupants of the community which they serve. &nbsp;It is our goal to provide you excellent service by identifying those activities, processes, or construction flaws which can lead to unwanted fires, and other types of accidents or emergencies.</p>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '[]', NULL, 'info', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'hide', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2016-02-11 20:01:16', '2016-03-01 18:36:13', '74aaea86-636b-4608-bb92-1e5dab19d9a3'),
 ('1582', '1802', 'en_us', 'Schedule Your Inspections with Public Works', '', '<p>Public works issues permits regarding construction around the area of your property including:</p>\r\n\r\n<ol><li>CGS&nbsp;(curb, gutter, sidewalk, encroachment)</li><li>X (excavations)</li><li>SL (Sewer Lateral)</li><li>P-Job (Infrastructure for larger projects around landscaping)</li></ol><p><br></p>\r\n\r\n<p>During stages of construction, you will need to schedule inspections with the Public Works department to make sure your space complies with these permits.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Public Works Department Hours</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Monday through Friday, 8:00AM to 5:00PM<br></p>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '[]', NULL, 'info', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'hide', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2016-02-11 20:07:45', '2016-03-01 18:36:13', '321d867e-bc6f-4eb3-bfc1-eca7162addd1'),
 ('1592', '1832', 'en_us', 'Schedule Inspections for your Business', '​The types of permits that are required for your business will dictate the types of inspections needed.​', '<p>Inspections are required to insure that the construction is proceeding according to the approved plans and project conditions-of-approval, and that all current code standards are being met. This will help to insure personal safety and to secure the value of the improvement.</p>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '[]', NULL, 'info', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'hide', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2016-02-11 20:11:36', '2016-03-01 18:36:13', 'd3c94657-09ac-44d1-90a1-255172403df1'),
