 ('1992', '2382', 'en_us', 'Dan Kalb', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '[]', NULL, 'info', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'hide', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Oakland is a wonderful place to live, but there are many challenges facing our city. As your council member, I will work hard with you and with my colleagues on the Council to solve problems with innovation, seek to instill a greater sense of community responsiveness in what comes out of City Hall, listen and pay attention to people\'s real-life concerns, and stay true to my strong sense of integrity and public service.', '<p>Dan has spent virtually his entire adult life as a public interest and environmental advocate, a policy manager, community service volunteer, and progressive reformer. He’s experienced in the policy-making process and knows how to work effectively with people to get things done.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>From 2003 to 2012, Dan was the California Policy Director for the Union of Concerned Scientists, working on a range of regional and statewide air quality, climate change, green jobs, renewable energy, and transportation issues.&nbsp; Previously, he worked for the Sierra Club, a Bay Area community college, and the nonprofit government reform group, Common Cause. In 2012, Dan served on the Youth Leadership and Community Safety task force for the Oakland Fund for Children & Youth (OFCY). He is also a board member of the Jewish Community Relations Council of the East Bay.&nbsp;<br><br></p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<p>Dan received a Baccalaureate of Science degree in Conservation of Natural Resources from U.C. Berkeley and a Masters of Public Administration (with an emphasis in Nonprofit Organization Management) from the University of San Francisco. Kalb also has ten years experience as a community mediator resolving neighborhood disputes. Dan and his wife Valarie live in the Rockridge/Temescal portion of District One.&nbsp;&nbsp;<br>Councilmember Kalb serves on the following City&nbsp;Council committees:</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<ul><li>Finance & Management (Chair)</li><li>Public Works</li><li>Public Safety</li><li>Rules & Legislation</li></ul>', NULL, '', '', 'dkalb@oaklandnet.com', '<p>(510) 238-7001</p>', '<p>1 Frank Ogawa Plaza, 2/F<br>Oakland, CA 94612</p>', '<p>Councilmember Kalb has Community Office Hours each month at rotating North Oakland cafés.&nbsp;District One resident can sign up for a 20-minute slot by emailing&nbsp;Monica Harris&nbsp;at&nbsp;<a href=\"mailto:mmharris@oaklandnet.com\">mmharris@oaklandnet.com</a>,&nbsp; 510-238-7014. Feel free to include the topic of your inquiry or issue when you reserve a spot.&nbsp;Thank you!<br>&nbsp;<br>You can also meet Councilmember Kalb every third Sunday at the Temescal Farmer\'s Market.<third sunday=\"\" at=\"\" the=\"\" temescal=\"\" farmer\'s=\"\" market=\"\"><br></third></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>March 5, 2016</strong><br>10:00 am -12:30 pm<br>Terrace Gifts and Coffee<br>5891 Broadway Terrace<br>&nbsp;<br><strong>April 2, 2016</strong><br>10:00 am -12:30 pm<br>MLK Cafe<br>3860 Martin Luther King Jr. Way<br>&nbsp;<br><strong>May 7, 2016</strong><br>10:00 am -12:30 pm<br>Old Brooklyn Bagels & Deli<br>6000 College Ave.<br>&nbsp;<br><strong>June 4, 2016</strong><br>10:00 am -12:30 pm<br>Nomad Café<br>6500 Shattuck Ave.<br></p>', 'Councilmember District One', NULL, NULL, '2016-03-01 00:10:06', '2016-03-01 18:36:17', 'a070102a-bab4-4884-abce-4046be9adfc9'),
