 Common Parking Violations<\\/a><\\/li><li><a href=\\\"http:\\/\\/www2.oaklandnet.com\\/oakca1\\/groups\\/ceda\\/documents\\/marketingmaterial\\/oak044797.pdf\\\">Complete roster of parking violation fines from the OMC and California Vehicle Code<\\/a><\\/li><li><a href=\\\"http:\\/\\/library.municode.com\\/index.aspx?clientId=16308&stateId=5&stateName=California\\\">Oakland Municipal Code about parking violations<\\/a><\\/li><li><a href=\\\"http:\\/\\/www.leginfo.ca.gov\\/cgi-bin\\/calawquery?codesection=veh\\\">California Vehicle Code<\\/a><\\/li><\\/ul>\",\"312\":{\"1372\":{\"type\":\"onlineLink\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"onlineTitle\":\"Online\",\"linkTitle\":\"Pay your ticket online\",\"linkUrl\":\"https:\\/\\/prodpci.etimspayments.com\\/pbw\\/include\\/oakland\\/input.jsp\",\"primaryCallToAction\":\"1\"}},\"1382\":{\"type\":\"phoneNumber\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"number\":\"1 (800) 500-6484\",\"primaryCallToAction\":\"\",\"phoneNumberTitle\":\"By Phone\"}},\"1392\":{\"type\":\"physicalAddress\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"physicalAddressTitle\":\"Mail In or Pay in Person\",\"address\":\"<p><strong>Parking Citation Assistance Center<\\/strong><br>250 Frank H. Ogawa Plaza, Suite 6300<br>Oakland, CA 94612<br><\\/p>\",\"primaryCallToAction\":\"\"}}},\"5\":\"\",\"92\":\"\",\"3\":\"\",\"4\":\"\"}}', '2016-02-10 20:48:31', '2016-02-10 20:48:31', '625cb99c-05a9-421b-9a3e-0859357ee0c4'),
 ('3092', '1092', '3', '1', 'en_us', '2', '', '{\"typeId\":\"3\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Check Your Building Plan\",\"slug\":\"check-your-building-plan\",\"postDate\":1454962860,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":\"1062\",\"fields\":{\"1\":\"<p>Once you have submitted all of your&nbsp;<a href=\\\"http:\\/\\/www2.oaklandnet.com\\/Government\\/o\\/PBN\\/OurServices\\/permits\\/index.htm\\\">required documents and building permit fees<\\/a>, our Building Services engineers will review your plans for&nbsp;<a href=\\\"http:\\/\\/www2.oaklandnet.com\\/Government\\/o\\/PBN\\/OurOrganization\\/BuildingServices\\/s\\/codes\\/index.htm\\\">compliance with applicable codes and regulations<\\/a>.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Plan check for new dwellings usually takes four to six weeks. However, plans with special engineering may take longer. Building Services will also submit your plans to the Fire Services agency for review. Fire review takes 1-10&nbsp;days.&nbsp;<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>When you apply for your&nbsp;<a href=\\\"http:\\/\\/www2.oaklandnet.com\\/Government\\/o\\/PBN\\/OurServices\\/permits\\/index.htm\\\">Building Permit<\\/a>, Zoning staff will review the plans submitted to ensure that all conditions of approval are satisfied and that the plans are consistent with Zoning approval.&nbsp;If we return your plans to you for revision and resubmittal, plan check time will increase accordingly. For answers to your plan check questions, please call (510) 238-3891.<\\/p>\",\"312\":{\"new1\":{\"type\":\"phoneNumber\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"number\":\"1 (510) 238-3891\",\"primaryCallToAction\":\"1\",\"phoneNumberTitle\":\"\"}}},\"5\":\"\",\"92\":\"\",\"3\":\"\",\"4\":\"\"}}', '2016-02-10 20:51:53', '2016-02-10 20:51:53', '763020fc-b886-4c82-b020-dd86d748e9f8'),
 ('3102', '932', '3', '1', 'en_us', '3', '', '{\"typeId\":\"3\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Start Your Utilities\",\"slug\":\"start-your-utilities\",\"postDate\":1453933500,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":\"1362\",\"fields\":{\"1\":\"<p>PG&E (Pacific Gas and Electric) is the local utility company. Make sure to contact PG&E as soon as you find your location to get all of your utilities in order.&nbsp; Depending on the services you need, you may need to wait for assistance. &nbsp;It is recommended that you get your requests in early.<\\/p>\",\"312\":{\"new1\":{\"type\":\"onlineLink\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"onlineTitle\":\"\",\"linkTitle\":\"Visit PG&E Online\",\"linkUrl\":\"http:\\/\\/pge.com\\/\",\"primaryCallToAction\":\"1\"}}},\"5\":\"\",\"92\":\"\",\"3\":\"\",\"4\":\"\"}}', '2016-02-10 20:54:40', '2016-02-10 20:54:40', '8026a1cb-ef32-4eec-9bb0-8c936f49d6b9'),
 ('3112', '6', '3', '1', 'en_us', '40', '', '{\"typeId\":\"3\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Pay a Parking Ticket\",\"slug\":\"pay-a-parking-ticket\",\"postDate\":1449259680,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":\"122\",\"fields\":{\"1\":\"<p>You have 21 days after the date the ticket was written to make a payment.&nbsp;Please have your&nbsp;credit card on hand&nbsp;(Visa, Mastercard, Discover or American Express)<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<h2>Parking Citation Assistance Center Hours<\\/h2>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Mondays, Tuesdays, Thursdays and Fridays from 9 a.m. to 4:30 p.m.<br>Wednesdays from 9:30 a.m. to 4:30 p.m.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<h2 id=\\\"ways-to-pay\\\">Additional In Person Locations<\\/h2>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><strong>Parking ticket payment kiosks<\\/strong><br>250 Frank H. Ogawa Plaza<br>Monday through Friday from 8:30 a.m. to 5 p.m.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><strong>Eastmont Police Substation<\\/strong><br>2651 73rd Avenue<br>Monday through Saturday from 8:00 a.m. to 4 p.m.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<h2>Refund Request Form<\\/h2>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>If you feel you are due a refund for overpayment for a parking ticket associated with your license plate, please complete and return a Refund Request Form.\\r\\nClick here to download the Refund Request Form.\\r\\nProvide proof of payment as detailed on the form.\\r\\nPlease allow four to six weeks for processing.\\r\\nCompleted forms and proof of payment can be submitted by mail, in person or by fax.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<h2>Additional References<\\/h2>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<ul><li><a href=\\\"https:\\/\\/beta.oaklandca.gov\\/services\\/parking\\/find-parking\\/costs-of-common-parking-violations#entry:332:url\\\">Costs of Common Parking Violations<\\/a><\\/li><li><a href=\\\"http:\\/\\/www2.oaklandnet.com\\/oakca1\\/groups\\/ceda\\/documents\\/marketingmaterial\\/oak044797.pdf\\\">Complete roster of parking violation fines from the OMC and California Vehicle Code<\\/a><\\/li><li><a href=\\\"http:\\/\\/library.municode.com\\/index.aspx?clientId=16308&stateId=5&stateName=California\\\">Oakland Municipal Code about parking violations<\\/a><\\/li><li><a href=\\\"http:\\/\\/www.leginfo.ca.gov\\/cgi-bin\\/calawquery?codesection=veh\\\">California Vehicle Code<\\/a><\\/li><\\/ul>\",\"312\":{\"1372\":{\"type\":\"onlineLink\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"onlineTitle\":\"Online\",\"linkTitle\":\"Pay your ticket online\",\"linkUrl\":\"https:\\/\\/prodpci.etimspayments.com\\/pbw\\/include\\/oakland\\/input.jsp\",\"primaryCallToAction\":\"1\"}},\"1382\":{\"type\":\"phoneNumber\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"number\":\"1 (800) 500-6484\",\"primaryCallToAction\":\"\",\"phoneNumberTitle\":\"By Phone\"}},\"1392\":{\"type\":\"physicalAddress\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"physicalAddressTitle\":\"Mail In or Pay in Person\",\"address\":\"<p><strong>Parking Citation Assistance Center<\\/strong><br>250 Frank H. Ogawa Plaza, Suite 6300<br>Oakland, CA 94612<br><\\/p>\",\"primaryCallToAction\":\"\"}}},\"5\":\"\",\"92\":\"\",\"3\":\"\",\"4\":\"\"}}', '2016-02-10 20:56:06', '2016-02-10 20:56:06', '9066fdf2-4ba9-441f-8c02-c0d2abcfc23e'),
 ('3122', '132', '3', '1', 'en_us', '5', '', '{\"typeId\":\"3\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Contest a Parking Ticket\",\"slug\":\"contest-a-parking-ticket\",\"postDate\":1450478580,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":\"122\",\"fields\":{\"1\":\"<p><a href=\\\"\\\">Download and complete the <\\/a><a href=\\\"http:\\/\\/www2.oaklandnet.com\\/oakca1\\/groups\\/cityadministrator\\/documents\\/form\\/oak041670.pdf\\\">Contest Form<\\/a> or write a letter of explanation for contesting your citation.\\r\\nPlease include your name, address, telephone number, current mailing address and parking ticket citation number.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Keep a copy of your ticket for your records.\\r\\nReturn your Contest Form or letter, along with the original parking ticket and additional documents in Person, by Mail, or by Fax.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<ul><li>Please wait 48 hours from the time of issuance to ensure your citation is entered into the online system.<\\/li><li>It may take handwritten tickets up to two weeks to be entered into the online system.<\\/li><li>You must contest your ticket within 21 days of the date of issuance.<\\/li><li>You\\u2019ll need to upload up to three documents that provide evidence to support your written testimony.<\\/li><\\/ul>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<h3 id=\\\"what-happens-next\\\">What Happens Next<\\/h3>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<ol>\\r\\n  <li>The Parking Citation Assistance Center investigates your ticket.<\\/li>\\r\\n  <li>You will be notified of the decision by mail.<\\/li>\\r\\n  <li>If the ticket is upheld, you will have 21 days to pay your ticket or request an Administrative Hearing.<\\/li>\\r\\n  <li>If you contested a parking ticket and you are not satisfied with the decision, you can <a href=\\\"https:\\/\\/beta.oaklandca.gov\\/services\\/parking\\/find-parking\\/request-an-administrative-hearing#entry:182:url\\\">request an Administrative Hearing<\\/a>.<\\/li>\\r\\n<\\/ol>\",\"312\":{\"1402\":{\"type\":\"onlineLink\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"onlineTitle\":\"Online\",\"linkTitle\":\"Contest online\",\"linkUrl\":\"https:\\/\\/wmq.etimspayments.com\\/pbw\\/include\\/oakland\\/dispute_request.jsp.\",\"primaryCallToAction\":\"1\"}},\"1412\":{\"type\":\"phoneNumber\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"number\":\"(510) 986-2699\",\"primaryCallToAction\":\"\",\"phoneNumberTitle\":\"By Fax\"}},\"1422\":{\"type\":\"physicalAddress\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"physicalAddressTitle\":\"In Person or By Mail\",\"address\":\"<p><strong>Parking Citation Assistance Center<\\/strong><br>250 Frank H. Ogawa Plaza, Suite 6300<br>Oakland, CA 94612<\\/p>\",\"primaryCallToAction\":\"\"}}},\"4\":\"\"}}', '2016-02-10 21:18:26', '2016-02-10 21:18:26', '55447f3c-c101-4edf-a8fe-d53e92c86a6a'),
 ('3132', '92', '3', '1', 'en_us', '3', '', '{\"typeId\":\"3\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Apply for a Residential Parking Permit\",\"slug\":\"apply-for-a-residential-parking-permit\",\"postDate\":1450476240,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":\"52\",\"fields\":{\"1\":\"<p>You can apply for a parking permit through the Residential Parking Permit (RPP) program. This permit will allow you park your vehicle in certain neighborhoods in Oakland. You need to register your vehicle to an eligible address to receive the permit.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<h3 id=\\\"what-you-need-to-know-before-applying\\\">What You Need to Know Before Applying<\\/h3>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<ol>\\r\\n  <li>To see if your address is eligible, go to__<strong>__<\\/strong><strong>__<\\/strong>_____<\\/li>\\r\\n  <li>Make sure your address on your vehicle\\u2019s registration and driver\\u2019s license is up to date.<ol><li>Click here to update your address with the DMV online. (http:\\/\\/dmv.ca.gov\\/online\\/onlinesvcs.htm)<\\/li><\\/ol><ol><li>After updating your address, print the confirmation.<\\/li><\\/ol><ol><li>Submit this confirmation with your application.<\\/li><\\/ol><\\/li>\\r\\n  \\r\\n  \\r\\n  \\r\\n  <li>Clear all unpaid parking tickets from the City of Oakland.<\\/li><\\/ol>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<h3 id=\\\"how-to-apply-for-a-residential-parking-permit\\\">How to Apply for a Residential Parking Permit<\\/h3>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>You need to submit an application, four supporting documents and the correct fee to apply. The address on your application must match the address on each supporting document.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<h3>Parking&nbsp;Citation&nbsp;Assistance Center&nbsp;Hours<\\/h3>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Mondays, Tuesdays, Thursdays and Fridays from 9 a.m. to 4:30 p.m.<br>Wednesdays from 9:30 a.m. to 4:30 p.m.<\\/p>\",\"312\":{\"1482\":{\"type\":\"onlineLink\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"onlineTitle\":\"\",\"linkTitle\":\"Download the permit application\",\"linkUrl\":\"http:\\/\\/www2.oaklandnet.com\\/Parking\\/OAK046014\",\"primaryCallToAction\":\"1\"}},\"1492\":{\"type\":\"physicalAddress\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"physicalAddressTitle\":\"Submit Your Application to:\",\"address\":\"<p><strong>Parking Citation Assistance Center<\\/strong><br>250 Frank H. Ogawa Plaza, Suite 6300<br>Oakland, CA 94612 Phone: (800) 500-6484<\\/p>\",\"primaryCallToAction\":\"\"}}},\"4\":\"\"}}', '2016-02-10 21:19:29', '2016-02-10 21:19:29', 'ff6e5218-6ab2-4d2f-9b80-f36d54682ed5'),
 ('3142', '112', '3', '1', 'en_us', '3', '', '{\"typeId\":\"3\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Renew Your Residential Parking Permit\",\"slug\":\"renew-your-residential-parking-permit\",\"postDate\":1450476960,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":\"52\",\"fields\":{\"1\":\"<p>You can renew your permit online if you received a letter that says you are eligible for online renewal.<\\/p>\",\"312\":{\"1502\":{\"type\":\"onlineLink\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"onlineTitle\":\"Online\",\"linkTitle\":\"Renew your permit online\",\"linkUrl\":\"https:\\/\\/pci.etimspayments.com\\/pbw\\/include\\/oakland\\/rppinput.jsp\",\"primaryCallToAction\":\"\"}},\"1512\":{\"type\":\"physicalAddress\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"physicalAddressTitle\":\"In Person or by Mail\",\"address\":\"<p>Attn: Residential Parking Permits<br><strong>Parking Citation Assistance Center<\\/strong><br>250 Frank H. Ogawa Plaza, Suite 6300<br>Oakland, CA 94612<\\/p>\",\"primaryCallToAction\":\"\"}}},\"4\":\"\"}}', '2016-02-10 21:19:57', '2016-02-10 21:19:57', '9afaca32-2e19-4ff3-8e35-4b6978d8e2a3'),
 ('3152', '62', '3', '1', 'en_us', '2', '', '{\"typeId\":\"3\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Apply for a Disabled Parking \\\"Blue Zone\\\"\",\"slug\":\"apply-for-a-disabled-parking-blue-zone\",\"postDate\":1450474800,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":\"52\",\"fields\":{\"1\":\"<h3>Disabled Parking Zone \\u201cBlue Zone\\u201d Program<\\/h3>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>A \\u201cblue zone\\u201d provides on-street parking for people with disabilities. The \\u201cblue zone\\u201d has a painted blue curb with a posted sign.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Residents and businesses can request \\u201cblue zones\\u201d from the Disabled Parking Zone program.<br>The City does not install \\u201cblue zones\\u201d for paratransit drop-off and pick-up.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>To learn more, please read the Policy summaries below.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><br><a href=\\\"http:\\/\\/www2.oaklandnet.com\\/oakca1\\/groups\\/pwa\\/documents\\/policy\\/oak051830.pdf\\\">Residential Blue Zone Policy Summary<br><\\/a><a href=\\\"http:\\/\\/www2.oaklandnet.com\\/oakca1\\/groups\\/pwa\\/documents\\/policy\\/oak051829.pdf\\\">Non-Residential Blue Zone Policy Summary<\\/a><\\/p>\",\"312\":{\"new1\":{\"type\":\"onlineLink\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"onlineTitle\":\"Online\",\"linkTitle\":\"Download the Residential Blue Zone Application\",\"linkUrl\":\"http:\\/\\/www2.oaklandnet.com\\/oakca1\\/groups\\/pwa\\/documents\\/form\\/oak051831.pdf\",\"primaryCallToAction\":\"1\"}},\"new2\":{\"type\":\"onlineLink\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"onlineTitle\":\"Online\",\"linkTitle\":\"Download the Non-Residential Blue Zone Application\",\"linkUrl\":\"http:\\/\\/www2.oaklandnet.com\\/oakca1\\/groups\\/pwa\\/documents\\/form\\/oak051832.pdf\",\"primaryCallToAction\":\"1\"}}},\"4\":\"\"}}', '2016-02-10 21:22:02', '2016-02-10 21:22:02', '2b7e539c-e561-45f9-8a8c-437797b5f826'),
 ('3162', '72', '3', '1', 'en_us', '2', '', '{\"typeId\":\"3\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Apply for a Parking Obstruction Permit\",\"slug\":\"apply-for-a-parking-obstruction-permit\",\"postDate\":1450475880,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":\"52\",\"fields\":{\"1\":\"<p>An Obstruction Permit allows you to park the pod, portable storage unit or moving truck in one site for a limited amount of time.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<h3 id=\\\"how-the-obstruction-permit-works\\\">How the Obstruction Permit Works<\\/h3>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<ul>\\r\\n  <li>The Obstruction Permit tells nearby property owners that they can not park in the permitted site for a limited amount of time.<\\/li>\\r\\n  <li>You may only block the street or right of way that you are moving from or to.<\\/li>\\r\\n  <li>You need to post the NO PARKING sign(s) that you receive with the Obstruction Permit at least 72 hours (3 days) before parking the portable storage unit or moving truck.<\\/li>\\r\\n<\\/ul>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<h3 id=\\\"how-to-apply-for-an-obstruction-permit\\\">How to Apply for an Obstruction Permit<\\/h3>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>You can only apply for an Obstruction Permit in person at the Permit Center. To avoid long line, visit the Permit Center early in the day before the busiest time from 11 a.m. to 4 p.m.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<ol>\\r\\n  <li>Please bring the following information.<\\/li>\\r\\n  <li>Site address.<\\/li>\\r\\n  <li>Dates required.<\\/li>\\r\\n  <li>Number of parking spaces required. One parking space is 25 feet long.<\\/li>\\r\\n  <li>Meter numbers if you are blocking parking meters<\\/li>\\r\\n  <li>Contact phone number for the company or person applying.<\\/li>\\r\\n  <li>If related to work requiring permit, please reference permit application number.<\\/li>\\r\\n  <li>Traffic control plan (only required if you need to block traffic)<\\/li>\\r\\n  <li>Refer to the Traffic Engineering website(http:\\/\\/www2.oaklandnet.com\\/Government\\/o\\/PWA\\/o\\/EC\\/o\\/TS\\/OAK026469).<\\/li>\\r\\n  <li>Visit the Permit Center<\\/li>\\r\\n  <li>Once you arrive at the Permit Center\\u2019s Information Counter, ask for an Obstruction Permit.<\\/li>\\r\\n  <li>When your number is called, proceed to the indicated counter.<\\/li>\\r\\n  <li>Provide the required information<\\/li>\\r\\n  <li>Pay the permit fee<\\/li>\\r\\n  <li>The Permit Center accepts cash, checks payable to the City of Oakland and most major credit cards.<\\/li>\\r\\n<\\/ol>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<h3 id=\\\"where-to-apply-for-an-obstruction-permit\\\">Permit Center Hours<\\/h3>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Mondays, Tuesdays, Thursdays and Fridays from 8 a.m. to 4 p.m. Wednesdays from 9:30 a.m. to 4 p.m.* *last Wednesday of each month from 10 a.m. to 4 p.m.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<h3 id=\\\"cost-of-the-obstruction-permit\\\">Cost of the Obstruction Permit<\\/h3>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>The cost of an Obstruction Permit varies. The cost depends on the period of time for the permit, the number of parking spaces required and the type of parking spaces blocked. \\r\\nFor more information, please call the Permit Center at (510) 238-3443.<\\/p>\",\"312\":{\"new1\":{\"type\":\"physicalAddress\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"physicalAddressTitle\":\"Apply In Person\",\"address\":\"<p><strong>Permit Center<\\/strong><br>250&nbsp;Frank H. Ogawa Plaza, 2nd Floor<br>Oakland, CA 94612<\\/p>\",\"primaryCallToAction\":\"\"}}},\"4\":\"\\u200bDo you need to block parking spaces or traffic? If your portable storage unit or moving truck will block parking on a public street or right of way, you will need an Obstruction Permit.\"}}', '2016-02-10 21:25:04', '2016-02-10 21:25:04', '5b6c24f7-658b-42cd-90fc-08f2bf34ba14'),
 ('3172', '72', '3', '1', 'en_us', '3', '', '{\"typeId\":\"3\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Apply for a Parking Obstruction Permit\",\"slug\":\"apply-for-a-parking-obstruction-permit\",\"postDate\":1450475880,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":\"52\",\"fields\":{\"1\":\"<p>An Obstruction Permit allows you to park the pod, portable storage unit or moving truck in one site for a limited amount of time.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<h3 id=\\\"how-the-obstruction-permit-works\\\">How the Obstruction Permit Works<\\/h3>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<ul>\\r\\n  <li>The Obstruction Permit tells nearby property owners that they can not park in the permitted site for a limited amount of time.<\\/li>\\r\\n  <li>You may only block the street or right of way that you are moving from or to.<\\/li>\\r\\n  <li>You need to post the NO PARKING sign(s) that you receive with the Obstruction Permit at least 72 hours (3 days) before parking the portable storage unit or moving truck.<\\/li>\\r\\n<\\/ul>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<h3 id=\\\"how-to-apply-for-an-obstruction-permit\\\">How to Apply for an Obstruction Permit<\\/h3>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>You can only apply for an Obstruction Permit in person at the Permit Center. To avoid long line, visit the Permit Center early in the day before the busiest time from 11 a.m. to 4 p.m.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<ol>\\r\\n  <li>Please bring the following information.<\\/li>\\r\\n  <li>Site address.<\\/li>\\r\\n  <li>Dates required.<\\/li>\\r\\n  <li>Number of parking spaces required. One parking space is 25 feet long.<\\/li>\\r\\n  <li>Meter numbers if you are blocking parking meters<\\/li>\\r\\n  <li>Contact phone number for the company or person applying.<\\/li>\\r\\n  <li>If related to work requiring permit, please reference permit application number.<\\/li>\\r\\n  <li>Traffic control plan (only required if you need to block traffic)<\\/li>\\r\\n  <li>Refer to the Traffic Engineering website(http:\\/\\/www2.oaklandnet.com\\/Government\\/o\\/PWA\\/o\\/EC\\/o\\/TS\\/OAK026469).<\\/li>\\r\\n  <li>Visit the Permit Center<\\/li>\\r\\n  <li>Once you arrive at the Permit Center\\u2019s Information Counter, ask for an Obstruction Permit.<\\/li>\\r\\n  <li>When your number is called, proceed to the indicated counter.<\\/li>\\r\\n  <li>Provide the required information<\\/li>\\r\\n  <li>Pay the permit fee<\\/li>\\r\\n  <li>The Permit Center accepts cash, checks payable to the City of Oakland and most major credit cards.<\\/li><\\/ol>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<h3 id=\\\"cost-of-the-obstruction-permit\\\">Cost of the Obstruction Permit<\\/h3>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>The cost of an Obstruction Permit varies. The cost depends on the period of time for the permit, the number of parking spaces required and the type of parking spaces blocked. \\r\\nFor more information, please call the Permit Center at (510) 238-3443.<\\/p>\",\"312\":{\"1622\":{\"type\":\"physicalAddress\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"physicalAddressTitle\":\"Apply In Person\",\"address\":\"<p><strong>Permit Center<\\/strong><br>250&nbsp;Frank H. Ogawa Plaza, 2nd Floor<br>Oakland, CA 94612<br><br>Mondays, Tuesdays, Thursdays and Fridays from 8 a.m. to 4 p.m.<br>Wednesdays from 9:30 a.m. to 4 p.m.<br>Last Wednesday of each month from 10 a.m. to 4 p.m.<br><\\/p>\",\"primaryCallToAction\":\"\"}}},\"4\":\"\\u200bDo you need to block parking spaces or traffic? If your portable storage unit or moving truck will block parking on a public street or right of way, you will need an Obstruction Permit.\"}}', '2016-02-10 21:25:54', '2016-02-10 21:25:54', 'd9bf64c0-cf77-42bd-ab38-4e92ce42d6c3'),
 ('3182', '222', '3', '1', 'en_us', '2', '', '{\"typeId\":\"3\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"What To Do If Your Car Is Booted\",\"slug\":\"what-to-do-if-your-car-is-booted\",\"postDate\":1450482540,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":\"322\",\"fields\":{\"1\":\"<h3>What to Know<\\/h3>\\r\\n\\r\\n<ul>\\r\\n  <li>Do not attempt to drive your vehicle because severe damage may occur.<\\/li><li>The parking boot program targets the most serious parking violators who have&nbsp;<strong>five (5) or more unpaid parking tickets<\\/strong>.<\\/li><li>A sticker will be displayed on a window of your vehicle showing that your vehicle has been booted.<\\/li>\\r\\n  <li>This sticker will include instructions in English, Chinese and Spanish.<\\/li><\\/ul>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<ul>\\r\\n  <li>Phone assistance is available in multiple languages.<\\/li>\\r\\n<\\/ul>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<h3 id=\\\"how-to-remove-the-boot-from-your-vehicle\\\">How to Remove the Boot from Your Vehicle<\\/h3>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Pay the fines for the unpaid tickets. You can make payments by phone or in person. In most cases, you can drive your vehicle in about five minutes. Payment plan options are available.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<h4>By Phone<\\/h4>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<ol>\\r\\n  <li>Pay the fines with a credit\\/debit card or e-check.<\\/li>\\r\\n  <li>The operator will provide a six-digit code.<\\/li>\\r\\n  <li>This six-digit code will allow removal of the boot without damage to your vehicle.<\\/li>\\r\\n  <li>Call the Help Center at (800) 500-6484 if you need assistance with boot removal steps.<\\/li>\\r\\n  <li>Return the boot to the location provided by the Help Center.<\\/li>\\r\\n<\\/ol>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<h4>In Person<\\/h4>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<ol>\\r\\n  <li>Pay the fines in cash.<\\/li>\\r\\n  <li>You will receive a six-digit code.<\\/li>\\r\\n  <li>This six-digit code will allow removal of the boot without damage to your vehicle.<\\/li>\\r\\n  <li>Call the Help Center if you need assistance with boot removal steps.<\\/li>\\r\\n  <li>Return the boot to the location provided by the Parking Assistance Center.<\\/li><\\/ol>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<h3>Hours<\\/h3>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Mondays, Tuesdays, Thursdays and Fridays from 9 a.m. to 4:30 p.m.<br>Wednesdays from 9:30 a.m. to 4:30 p.m.<\\/p>\",\"312\":{\"new1\":{\"type\":\"phoneNumber\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"phoneNumberTitle\":\"Call the Help Center\",\"number\":\"1 (800) 500-6484\",\"primaryCallToAction\":\"1\"}},\"new2\":{\"type\":\"physicalAddress\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"physicalAddressTitle\":\"In Person\",\"address\":\"<p><strong>Parking&nbsp;Citation Assistance&nbsp;Center<\\/strong><br>250 Frank H. Ogawa Plaza, Suite 6300<br>Oakland, CA 94612<\\/p>\",\"primaryCallToAction\":\"\"}}},\"4\":\"\"}}', '2016-02-10 21:32:21', '2016-02-10 21:32:21', 'd640b79b-1425-4edc-96d4-7e8243da6f82'),
 ('3192', '222', '3', '1', 'en_us', '3', '', '{\"typeId\":\"3\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Remove the Boot from a Booted Vehicle\",\"slug\":\"what-to-do-if-your-car-is-booted\",\"postDate\":1450482540,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":\"322\",\"fields\":{\"1\":\"<h3>What to Know<\\/h3>\\r\\n\\r\\n<ul>\\r\\n  <li>Do not attempt to drive your vehicle because severe damage may occur.<\\/li><li>The parking boot program targets the most serious parking violators who have&nbsp;<strong>five (5) or more unpaid parking tickets<\\/strong>.<\\/li><li>A sticker will be displayed on a window of your vehicle showing that your vehicle has been booted.<\\/li>\\r\\n  <li>This sticker will include instructions in English, Chinese and Spanish.<\\/li><\\/ul>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<ul>\\r\\n  <li>Phone assistance is available in multiple languages.<\\/li>\\r\\n<\\/ul>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<h3 id=\\\"how-to-remove-the-boot-from-your-vehicle\\\">How to Remove the Boot from Your Vehicle<\\/h3>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Pay the fines for the unpaid tickets. You can make payments by phone or in person. In most cases, you can drive your vehicle in about five minutes. Payment plan options are available.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<h4>By Phone<\\/h4>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<ol>\\r\\n  <li>Pay the fines with a credit\\/debit card or e-check.<\\/li>\\r\\n  <li>The operator will provide a six-digit code.<\\/li>\\r\\n  <li>This six-digit code will allow removal of the boot without damage to your vehicle.<\\/li>\\r\\n  <li>Call the Help Center at (800) 500-6484 if you need assistance with boot removal steps.<\\/li>\\r\\n  <li>Return the boot to the location provided by the Help Center.<\\/li>\\r\\n<\\/ol>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<h4>In Person<\\/h4>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<ol>\\r\\n  <li>Pay the fines in cash.<\\/li>\\r\\n  <li>You will receive a six-digit code.<\\/li>\\r\\n  <li>This six-digit code will allow removal of the boot without damage to your vehicle.<\\/li>\\r\\n  <li>Call the Help Center if you need assistance with boot removal steps.<\\/li>\\r\\n  <li>Return the boot to the location provided by the Parking Assistance Center.<\\/li><\\/ol>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<h3>Hours<\\/h3>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Mondays, Tuesdays, Thursdays and Fridays from 9 a.m. to 4:30 p.m.<br>Wednesdays from 9:30 a.m. to 4:30 p.m.<\\/p>\",\"312\":{\"1632\":{\"type\":\"phoneNumber\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"phoneNumberTitle\":\"Call the Help Center\",\"number\":\"1 (800) 500-6484\",\"primaryCallToAction\":\"1\"}},\"1642\":{\"type\":\"physicalAddress\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"physicalAddressTitle\":\"In Person\",\"address\":\"<p><strong>Parking&nbsp;Citation Assistance&nbsp;Center<\\/strong><br>250 Frank H. Ogawa Plaza, Suite 6300<br>Oakland, CA 94612<\\/p>\",\"primaryCallToAction\":\"\"}}},\"4\":\"\"}}', '2016-02-10 21:33:58', '2016-02-10 21:33:58', '1d52025a-d224-4f0b-8c68-479a11c6473e'),
 ('3202', '232', '3', '1', 'en_us', '2', '', '{\"typeId\":\"3\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Getting Your Towed Vehicle Released\",\"slug\":\"what-to-do-if-your-car-is-towed\",\"postDate\":1450482600,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":\"322\",\"fields\":{\"1\":\"<p>If you believe your vehicle has been towed, please call A&B Vehicle Processing at (510) 635-3211 or visit <a href=\\\"http:\\/\\/www.abimpound.com.\\/towed.html\\\">http:\\/\\/www.abimpound.com.\\/towed.html<\\/a> to confirm.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<h3 id=\\\"what-to-know\\\">What to Know<\\/h3>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>A vehicle can be towed in Oakland for any of the following reasons:<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<ul>\\r\\n  <li>A boot is placed on the vehicle, and payment for the boot fee and parking tickets have not been received<\\/li>\\r\\n  <li>A vehicle registration (plate tag) has been expired for more than six (6) months<\\/li>\\r\\n  <li>A vehicle has more than $2,500 in unpaid parking tickets<\\/li>\\r\\n  <li>A vehicle has five (5) or more unpaid tickets in the State of California<\\/li>\\r\\n<\\/ul>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<h3 id=\\\"how-to-get-your-vehicle-released\\\">How to Get Your Vehicle Released<\\/h3>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<ol>\\r\\n  <li>Pay all of your unpaid parking tickets in Oakland. Payment plans are not available for towed vehicles.<\\/li>\\r\\n  <li>Visit or call the Parking Citation Assistance Center to make payments.<\\/li>\\r\\n  <li>Pay fees for towing and storage directly to the tow company.<\\/li>\\r\\n  <li>You may need to pay unpaid tickets from all other cities in California to have your vehicle released.<\\/li>\\r\\n<\\/ol>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<h3 id=\\\"for-more-information\\\">For More Information<\\/h3>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<table>\\r\\n<thead>\\r\\n<tr><th>Location<\\/th><th>Hours<\\/th><\\/tr>\\r\\n<\\/thead>\\r\\n<tbody>\\r\\n<tr><td style=\\\"background-color:white\\\">\\r\\nParking Citation Assistance Center\\r\\n\\r\\n250 Frank H. Ogawa Plaza, Suite 6300\\r\\n\\r\\nOakland, CA 94612\\r\\n\\r\\nPhone: (800) 500-6484\\r\\n<\\/td><td>\\r\\nMondays, Tuesdays, Thursdays and Fridays from 9 a.m. to 4:30 p.m.\\r\\nWednesdays from 9:30 a.m. to 4:30 p.m.\\r\\n<\\/td><\\/tr>\\r\\n<\\/tbody>\\r\\n<\\/table>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Only the registered owner of the towed vehicle can contest one or more of the unpaid tickets.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Please visit the Parking Citation Assistance Center at 250 Frank H. Ogawa Plaza, Suite 6300 or call the Center at (510) 238-4484.<\\/p>\",\"312\":\"\",\"4\":\"\"}}', '2016-02-10 21:34:11', '2016-02-10 21:34:11', '51f4d711-9b3f-4ffb-a071-d3ba360508f7'),
 ('3212', '322', '3', '1', 'en_us', '4', '', '{\"typeId\":\"4\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Dealing with Booted or Towed Cars\",\"slug\":\"what-to-do-with-booted-or-towed-cars\",\"postDate\":1450486140,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":\"5\",\"fields\":{\"4\":\"Steps to take and who to contact if your car is booted or towed\",\"282\":\"\"}}', '2016-02-10 21:34:31', '2016-02-10 21:34:31', '9b3dc526-7db3-47b1-bc0a-f5b7865aaf7c'),
