 ('312', 'field', '1', 'en_us', ' you may qualify for a disabled person placard or license plates if you have one or more of the conditions below inability to use one or more lower limbs or both hands diagnosed disease that impairs or interferes with mobility severe disability that leaves you unable to move without an assistive device documented problems with your eyesight such as lower vision or partial sightedness the city of oakland does not issue disabled person placards or license plates illegal use of disabled parking only the disabled driver issued the placard or plates can use the parking placard or plates a driver that does any of the actions below can receive tickets and fines lend your disabled person placard to someone else use someone else s disabled person placard have or display a fake disabled person placard or license plates report illegal use of disabled person placards and plates please call parking enforcement at 510 238 3099 '),
